", test_name, "HU").\nget Mobile device bluetooth name with adb shell settings get secure bluetooth_name.\ncreate Mobile device object with phone = create_device(Mobile1,mobile_name).\nclick Bluetooth icon from HU display with x,y = find_icon_in_screenshot(f"{path}/screenshot.png",f"{path}/helpers/Bluetooth.png") or x,y = find_icon_in_screenshot(f"{path}/screenshot.png",f"{path}/helpers/Bluetooth_2.png").\nclick Manage Devices Button from HU display with found = click_on_device(HU,"Manage devices").\nclick Smartphones Button on from HU display with found = click_on_device(HU,"Smartphones").\nrun the following function on Mobile device: phone.enable_airplane_mode_command() to simulate putting Mobile Device in shielding bag or shielding chamber. Wait 5 seconds with airplane mode enabled.\nrun the following function on Mobile device: phone.disable_airplane_mode_command() to disable airplane mode.\nrun the following function on Mobile device: phone.run_linkloss_command() to simulate getting Mobile Device out of shielding bag or shielding chamber. Wait 15 seconds for bluetooth connection to be re-established.\ncheck if "Connected" word can be found on HU display with found = find_word_on_device(HU,"Connected"). If it was found then Bluetooth connection is re-established and Phone icon on display of HU is visible and the test is Passed. If not then Bluetooth connection was not re-established after removing from shielding and the test is failed.\nplease make a screenshot on HU screen and save it on the path D:\\traget\\IDCevo\\IOP_configuration\\Test_results\\Screenshots.\nsave in Excel the status of the test (passed or failed) with the corresponding message.\nrun the following commmands after test is done in order to return to home menu: HU commands: adb shell input keyevent 3 one time; adb shell rm /sdcard/*.png.\nstop screen recordings on HU after test is done with stop_screen_recording("HU") and keep them if test is failed or delete them if test is passed.\n'}, {'Test 