ed) with the corresponding message.\nrun the following commmands after test is done in order to return to home menu: HU commands: adb shell input keyevent 3 one time; adb shell rm /sdcard/*.png.\nstop screen recordings on HU and Mobile after test is done with stop_screen_recording("HU") and keep them if test is failed or delete them if test is passed.'}, {'Test Case Description': '1 On HU go to Communication --> Contacts.\n2 Scroll to contact with same name and last name. CheIDCEvo if the 2 different phone numbers are merged into one contact.\n', 'Test Case Expected Result': '2 Contacts with the same name are merged. ', 'Test Case ID': 172992, 'Test Case Precondition': 'Mobile Device and HU are connected.\nPhonebook download is finished.\n2 contacts with same name and last name but 2 different telephone numbers.\n', 'Test Name': 'Merge_same_name', 'Test Script Description': 'check USB Matrix status with status = USB_Matrix_Status().\nget serial numbers for them with HU, Mobile1 = get_serial_number().\ncreate recordings folder with create_recordings_folder() and start screen recording for HU with start_screen_recording(f"-s {HU}", test_name, "HU")(example for HU).\nget Mobile device bluetooth name with adb shell settings get secure bluetooth_name.\ncreate Mobile device object with phone = create_device(Mobile1,mobile_name).\nclick Mobile device name button with regex from HU display with found = click_on_device_regex(HU, mobile_name).\nclick Contacts Button on from HU display with found = click_on_device(HU, "Contacts").\nrun the following function on mobile device: stdout = phone.get_contacts_name_command(). Extract the display_name for all contacts displayed in a list.\nCheck if a Contact  from the list appearing more than one time. Check if the contact last name is available with stdout = phone.get_contacts_data3_command() and if it is save it in a variable. If not save the whole name in a variable with stdout = phone.get_contacts_data2_command().\ncheck how many 