ay with found = click_on_device_regex(HU, click_target) or found = click_on_device_with_verification(HU, click_target). If it was not found run the following adb command: adb shell input swipe 1700 700 2000 200 to scroll down on contacts list from HU display. Try it for 10 times if the extracted contact was not found the test is failed.\nrun the following function on mobile device: stdout = phone.check_contacts_photo_data_command(contact_id).\ncheck if data15=BLOB word can be found in the command response with regex. If it was found then Mobile device Contact Picture is displayed successfully on HU and the test is Passed. If not then Mobile device Contact Picture is not displayed and the test is failed.\nplease make a screenshot on HU screen and save it on the path D:\\traget\\IDCevo\\IOP_configuration\\Test_results\\Screenshots.\nrun the following adb command on HU: adb shell input keyevent 3.\nclick Mobile device name button with regex from HU display with found = click_on_device_regex(HU, mobile_name).\nrun the following adb command on HU display: adb shell input swipe 1700 700 200 2500.\nsave in Excel the status of the test (passed or failed) with the corresponding message.\nrun the following commmands after test is done in order to return to home menu: HU commands: adb shell input keyevent 3 one time; adb shell rm /sdcard/*.png.\nstop screen recordings on HU and Mobile after test is done with stop_screen_recording("HU") and keep them if test is failed or delete them if test is passed.'}, {'Test Case Description': '1 While phonebook is downloading start audio playbaIDCEvo from Mobile Device.', 'Test Case Expected Result': '1 Audio playbaIDCEvo does not interrupt phonebook download.', 'Test Case ID': 172984, 'Test Case Precondition': 'Mobile Device and HU are connected.\nPhonebook download has started and is not finished.\nIn case the download of the phonebook is already finished, then delete Mobile Device on HU', 'Test Name': 'Audio_playback_during_phonebook_dow