\nclick Manage Devices Button from HU display with found = click_on_device(HU,"Manage devices").\nclick Smartphones Button on from HU display with found = click_on_device(HU,"Smartphones").\ncreate Mobile device object with phone = create_device(Mobile1,mobile_name).\nrun the following function on Mobile device phone.run_reboot_command(). Wait 60 seconds for Mobile device to reboot.\nrun adb command: adb shell input keyevent 3 on Mobile device to go to home menu.\nclick Not now Button on from HU display with found = click_on_device(HU,"Not now").\ncheck if "Connected" word can be found on HU display with found = find_word_on_device(HU,"Connected"). If it was found then HU has been reconnected successfully with Mobile device after Mobile device Power off and the test is Passed. If not then Mobile device has not been reconnected with HU after Mobile device Power off and the test is failed.\nplease make a screenshot on HU screen and save it on the path D:\\traget\\IDCevo\\IOP_configuration\\Test_results\\Screenshots. \nsave in Excel the status of the test (passed or failed) with the corresponding message.\nrun the following commmands after test is done in order to return to home menu: HU commands: adb shell input keyevent 3 one time; adb shell rm /sdcard/*.png.\nstop screen recordings on HU after test is done with stop_screen_recording("HU") and keep them if test is failed or delete them if test is passed.'}, {'Test Case Description': '1 On HU press COM button on ZBE or go to Communication -> Manage mobile devices -> scroll down to Manage mobile devices.\n2 Select connected device and press center button of ZBE.\nDelete connected device.\n\n\n', 'Test Case Expected Result': '2 Bluetooth connection is released.\nMobile Device 1 is not listed in HU anymore.\n3. Undo snaIDCEvobar should be displayer after cliIDCEvoing on remove option\n', 'Test Case ID': 172972, 'Test Case Precondition': 'Mobile Device and HU are connected.', 'Test Name': 'Delete_Mobile_Device_on_HU', 'Test Script Description': 'check USB Matrix status with status = USB_Matrix_Status().\nget serial numbers for them with HU, Mobile1 = get_serial_number().\ncreate recordings folder with create_recordings_folder() and start screen recording for HU and for Mobile Device with start_screen_recording(f"-s {HU}", test_name, "HU")(example for HU).\nget Mobile device bluetooth name with adb shell settings get secure bluetooth_name.\ncreate Mobile device object with phone = create_device(Mobile1,mobile_name).\nclick Bluetooth icon from HU display with x,y = find_icon_in_screenshot(f"{path}/screenshot.png",f"{path}/helpers/Bluetooth.png") or x,y = find_icon_in_screenshot(f"{path}/screenshot.png",f"{path}/helpers/Bluetooth_2.png")\nclick Manage Devices Button from HU display with found = click_on_device(HU,"Manage devices").\nclick Smartphones Button on from HU display with found = click_on_device(HU,"Smartphones").\nclick Mobile Menu Button icon from HU display with x,y = find_icon_in_screenshot(f"{path}/screenshot.png",f"{path}/helpers/Mobile_Menu_Button.png") or x,y = find_icon_in_screenshot(f"{path}/screenshot.png",f"{path}/helpers/Mobile_Menu_Button_2.png")\nclick Remove device Button with regex on from HU display with found = click_on_device_regex(HU,"Remove device").\ncheck if "Connected" word can be found on HU display. If it was found then Mobile device has not been deleted from HU Bluetooth devices list and the test is failed. If not then Mobile device has been deleted successfully from HU Bluetooth devices list and the test is Passed.\nplease make a screenshot on HU screen and save it on the path D:\\traget\\IDCevo\\IOP_configuration\\Test_results\\Screenshots. \nrun adb command: adb shell input keyevent 3 on HU to go to home menu.\nrun the following function on Mobile device: phone.click_close_button_popup() to click Close button for pop ups that may appear on screen.\nrun the following function on Mobile device: rc = phone.run_turn_screen_on_command() to turn Mobile screen on.\nrun the following function on Mobile device: rc = phone.run_unlock_screen_command() to unlock Mobile screen.\nrun the following function on Mobile device: phone.run_settings_menu_command() go to Mobile Settings menu.\nrun the following function on Mobile device: rc = phone.run_bluetooth_menu_command() go to Mobile Bluetooth menu.\nrun the following function on Mobile device: phone.click_settings_icon() to click on Settings icon for connected Bluetooth device.\nrun the following function on Mobile device: phone.click_unpair_button() to unpair Mobile device with connected Bluetooth device.\nrun the following function on Mobile device: phone.disable_bluetooth() to disable Bluetooth of Mobile device.\nsave in Excel the status of the test (passed or failed) with the corresponding message.\nrun the following commmands after test is done in order to return to home menu: HU commands: adb shell input keyevent 3 one time; adb shell rm /sdcard/*.png; Mobile device commands: rc = phone.run_home_command().\nstop screen recordings on HU and Mobile after test is done with stop_screen_recording("HU") and keep them if test is failed or delete them if test is passed.\n'}, {'Test Case Description': '1. CliIDCEvo on MD in HMI in order to connect or disconnect it\n\n', 'Test Case Expected Result': '1. MD disconnects or connects to the bench', 'Test Case ID': 172971, 'Test Case Precondition': 'Mobile Device and HU are connected.', 'Test Name': 'On_Tap_MD_connect_disconnect', 'Test Script Description': 'check USB Matrix status with status = USB_Matrix_Status().\nget serial numbers for them with HU, Mobile1 = get_serial_number().\ncreate recordings folder with create_recordings_folder() and start screen recording for HU with start_screen_recording(f"-s {HU}", test_name, "HU")(example for HU).\nget Mobile device bluetooth name with adb shell settings get secure bluetooth_name.\nclick Bluetooth icon from HU display with x,y = find_icon_in_screenshot(f"{path}/screenshot.png",f"{path}/helpers/Bluetooth.png") or x,y = find_icon_in_screenshot(f"{path}/screenshot.png",f"{path}/helpers/Bluetooth_2.png")\nclick Manage Devices Button from HU display with found = click_on_device(HU,"Manage devices").\nclick Smartphones Button on from HU display with found = click_on_device(HU,"Smartphones").\nclick Mobile device name button from HU display with found = click_on_device(HU,mobile_name).\ncheck if Mobile device name word can be found on HU display with found = find_word_on_device(HU,mobile_name). If it was found then Mobile device is present on HU bluetooth devices list and is disconnected. If not then Mobile device is not present on HU bluetooth devices list and the test is failed.\nplease make a screenshot on HU screen and save it on the path D:\\traget\\IDCevo\\IOP_configuration\\Test_results\\Screenshots. \nclick Mobile device name button with verification from HU display with found = click_on_device_with_verification(HU,mobile_name).\nclick Not now Button on from HU display with found = click_on_device(HU,"Not now").\ncheck if "Connected" word can be found on HU display with found = find_word_on_device(HU,"Connected"). If it was found then HU has been disconnected and reconnected successfully with Mobile device and the test is Passed. If not then Mobile device has not been reconnected with HU and the test is failed.\nsave in Excel the status of the test (passed or failed) with the corresponding message.\nrun the following commmands after test is done in order to return to home menu: HU commands: adb shell input keyevent 3 one time; adb shell rm /sdcard/*.png.\nstop screen recordings on HU after test is done with stop_screen_recording("HU") and keep them if test is failed or delete them if test is passed.'}, {'Test Case Description': '1 Activate Bluetooth on Mobile Device.\nIn order to be visible for other Bluetooth devices you have to enter the Bluetooth settings menu of your mobile device.\n\nOn HU press COM button on ZBE or go to Communication -> Manage mobile devices -> scroll down to Manage mobile devices -> select Connect new device. -> Select function Telephone.\n2 On Mobile Device 1 select HU.\n3 Wait for pairing timeout.\n', 'Test Case Expected Result': '1 HU can be found while Mobile Device 1 is searching for devices.\n2 Bluetooth pairing request screen shows up on Mobile Device 1 and HU.\nPIN code shown on both sides are the same.\nHU remains stable.\n3 Pairing process is terminated.\n', 'Test Case ID': 172970, 'Test Case Precondition': 'Mobile Device 1 isn`t paired with HU\nInfo: If Mobile Device and HU have been paired before, then delete Mobile Device on HU and HU on Mobile Device.', 'Test Name': 'Pairing_Timeout', 'Test Script Description': 'check USB Matrix status with status = USB_Matrix_Status().\nget serial numbers for them with HU, Mobile1 = get_serial_number().\ncreate recordings folder with create_recordings_folder() and start screen recording for HU and for Mobile Device with start_screen_recording(f"-s {HU}", test_name, "HU")(example for HU).\nget Mobile device bluetooth name with adb shell settings get secure bluetooth_name.\ncreate Mobile device object with phone = create_device(Mobile1,mobile_name).\nrun the following function on Mobile device: phone.click_close_button_popup() to click Close button for pop ups that may appear on screen.\nrun the following function on Mobile device: rc = phone.run_turn_screen_on_command() to turn Mobile screen on.\nrun the following function on Mobile device: rc = phone.run_unlock_screen_command() to unlock Mobile screen.\nrun the following function on Mobile device: phone.run_settings_menu_command() go to Mobile Settings menu.\nrun the following function on Mobile device: rc = phone.run_bluetooth_menu_command() go to Mobile Bluetooth menu.\nclick Bluetooth icon from HU display with x,y = find_icon_in_screenshot(f"{path}/screenshot.png",f"{path}/helpers/Bluetooth.png") or x,y = find_icon_in_screenshot(f"{path}/screenshot.png",f"{path}/helpers/Bluetooth_2.png")\nclick Manage Devices Button from HU display with found = click_on_device(HU,"Manage devices").\nclick Not now Button from HU display with found = click_on_device(HU,"Not now").\nclick Smartphones Button on from HU display with found = click_on_device(HU,"Smartphones").\nrun the following function on Mobile device: phone.click_close_button_popup() to click Close button for pop ups that may appear on screen.\nrun the following function on Mobile device: phone.enable_bluetooth() to enable Bluetooth for Mobile.\nrun the following function on Mobile device: phone.click_close_button_popup() to click Close button for pop ups that may appear on screen.\nclick Cancel Button from HU display with found = click_on_device(HU,"Cancel"). It may not appear everytime so we don\'t have an assert check for it.\nextract bluetooth_device_name for HU in a variable using the following adb command: adb shell dumpsys bluetooth_manager | findstr -i "Name:".\nclick bluetooth_device_name button with regex from Mobile device display with found = phone.click_HU_bluetooth_name_button(bluetooth_device_name). This is the name of HU device we have to connect with Mobile.\nWait for Pairing timeout 30s.\ncheck if "Try" word can be found on HU display with regex with found = find_word_on_device_via_regex(HU,"Try"). If it was found then Pairing timeout was reached in maximum 30s and the test is Passed. If not then Pairing timeout was not reached in maximum 30s and the test is failed.\nplease make a screenshot on HU screen and save it on the path D:\\traget\\IDCevo\\IOP_configuration\\Test_results\\Screenshots. \nclick OK button from Mobile device display with phone.click_OK_button(). It may not appear everytime so we don\'t have an assert check for it.\nrun the following function on Mobile device: phone.disable_bluetooth() to disable Bluetooth of Mobile device.\nsave in Excel the status of the test (passed or failed) with the corresponding message.\nrun the following commmands after test is done in order to return to home menu: HU commands: adb shell input keyevent 3 one time; adb shell rm /sdcard/*.png; Mobile device commands: rc = phone.run_home_command().\nstop screen recordings on HU and Mobile after test is done with stop_screen_recording("HU") and keep them if test is failed or delete them if test is passed.'}, {'Test Case Description': '1 Activate Bluetooth on Mobile Device.\nIn order to be visible for other Bluetooth devices you have to enter the Bluetooth settings menu of your mobile device.\n\nOn HU press COM button on ZBE or go to Communication -> Manage mobile devices -> scroll down to Manage mobile devices -> select Connect new device. -> Select function Telephone.\n2 On Mobile Device 1 select HU.\n3 Deny pairing on Mobile Device 1.\n', 'Test Case Expected Result': '1 HU can be found while Mobile Device 1 is searching for devices.\n2 Bluetooth pairing request screen shows up on Mobile Device 1 and HU.\nPIN code shown on both sides are the same.\nHU remains stable.\n3 Pairing process is terminated.\n', 'Test Case ID': 172969, 'Test Case Precondition': 'Mobile Device 1 isn`t paired with HU.', 'Test Name': 'Pairing_Denied_Mobile_Device', 'Test Script Description': 'check USB Matrix status with status = USB_Matrix_Status().\nget serial numbers for them with HU, Mobile1 = get_serial_number().\ncreate recordings folder with create_recordings_folder() and start screen recording for HU and for Mobile Device with start_screen_recording(f"-s {HU}", test_name, "HU")(example for HU).\nget Mobile device bluetooth name with adb shell settings get secure bluetooth_name.\ncreate Mobile device object with phone = create_device(Mobile1,mobile_name).\nrun the following function on Mobile device: phone.click_close_button_popup() to click Close button for pop ups that may appear on screen.\nrun the following function on Mobile device: rc = phone.run_turn_screen_on_command() to turn Mobile screen on.\nrun the following function on Mobile device: rc = phone.run_unlock_screen_command() to unlock Mobile screen.\nrun the following function on Mobile device: phone.run_settings_menu_command() go to Mobile Settings menu.\nrun the following function on Mobile device: rc = phone.run_bluetooth_menu_command() go to Mobile Bluetooth menu.\nclick Bluetooth icon from HU display with x,y = find_icon_in_screenshot(f"{path}/screenshot.png",f"{path}/helpers/Bluetooth.png") or x,y = find_icon_in_screenshot(f"{path}/screenshot.png",f"{path}/helpers/Bluetooth_2.png").\nclick Manage Devices Button from HU display with found = click_on_device(HU,"Manage devices").\nclick Not now Button from HU display with found = click_on_device(HU,"Not now").\nclick Smartphones Button on from HU display with found = click_on_device(HU,"Smartphones").\nrun the following function on Mobile device: phone.click_close_button_popup() to click Close button for pop ups that may appear on screen.\nrun the following function on Mobile device: phone.enable_bluetooth() to enable Bluetooth for Mobile.\nrun the following function on Mobile device: phone.click_close_button_popup() to click Close button for pop ups that may appear on screen.\nextract bluetooth_device_name for HU in a variable using the following adb command: adb shell dumpsys bluetooth_manager | findstr -i "Name:".\nclick bluetooth_device_name button with regex from Mobile device display with found = phone.click_HU_bluetooth_name_button(bluetooth_device_name). This is the name of HU device we have to connect with Mobile.\nclick Cancel button from Mobile device display with found = phone.click_Cancel_button().\ncheck if "Try" word can be found on HU display with regex with found = find_word_on_device_via_regex(HU,"Try"). If it was found then Pairing was denied successfully by Mobile device and the test is Passed. If not then Pairing denied by Mobile device doesn\'t work properly and the test is failed.\nplease make a screenshot on HU screen and save it on the path D:\\traget\\IDCevo\\IOP_configuration\\Test_results\\Screenshots. \nclick Cancel button from HU display with found = click_on_device(HU,"Cancel").\nclick OK button from Mobile device display with phone.click_OK_button(). It may not appear everytime so we don\'t have an assert check for it.\nrun the following function on Mobile device: phone.disable_bluetooth() to disable Bluetooth of Mobile device.\nsave in Excel the status of the test (passed or failed) with the corresponding message.\nrun the following commmands after test is done in order to return to home menu: HU commands: adb shell input keyevent 3 one time; adb shell rm /sdcard/*.png; Mobile device commands: rc = phone.run_home_command().\nstop screen recordings on HU and Mobile after test is done with stop_screen_recording("HU") and keep them if test is failed or delete them if test is passed.'}, {'Test Case Description': '1 Activate Bluetooth on Mobile Device.\nIn order to be visible for other Bluetooth devices you have to enter the Bluetooth settings menu of your mobile device.\n\nOn HU press COM button on ZBE or go to Communication -> Manage mobile devices -> scroll down to Manage mobile devices -> select Connect new device. -> Select function Telephone.\n2 On Mobile Device 1 select HU.\n3 Deny pairing on HU.\n', 'Test Case Expected Result': '1 HU can be found while Mobile Device 1 is searching for devices.\n2 Bluetooth pairing request screen shows up on Mobile Device 1 and HU.\nPIN code shown on both sides are the same.\nHU remains stable.\n3 Pairing process is terminated.\n', 'Test Case ID': 172968, 'Test Case Precondition': 'Mobile Device 1 isn`t paired with HU.', 'Test Name': 'Pairing_Denied_HU', 'Test Script Description': 'check USB Matrix status with status = USB_Matrix_Status().\nget serial numbers for them with HU, Mobile1 = get_serial_number().\ncreate recordings folder with create_recordings_folder() and start screen recording for HU and for Mobile Device with start_screen_recording(f"-s {HU}", test_name, "HU")(example for HU).\nget Mobile device bluetooth name with adb shell settings get secure bluetooth_name.\ncreate Mobile device object with phone = create_device(Mobile1,mobile_name).\nrun the following function on Mobile device: phone.click_close_button_popup() to click Close button for pop ups that may appear on screen.\nrun the following function on Mobile device: rc = phone.run_turn_screen_on_command() to turn Mobile screen on.\nrun the following function on Mobile device: rc = phone.run_unlock_screen_command() to unlock Mobile screen.\nrun the following function on Mobile device: phone.run_settings_menu_command() go to Mobile Settings menu.\nrun the following function on Mobile device: rc = phone.run_bluetooth_menu_command() go to Mobile Bluetooth menu.\nclick Bluetooth icon from HU display with x,y = find_icon_in_screenshot(f"{path}/screenshot.png",f"{path}/helpers/Bluetooth.png") or x,y = find_icon_in_screenshot(f"{path}/screenshot.png",f"{path}/helpers/Bluetooth_2.png")\nclick Manage Devices Button from HU display with found = click_on_device(HU,"Manage devices").\nclick Not now Button from HU display with found = click_on_device(HU,"Not now").\nclick Smartphones Button on from HU display with found = click_on_device(HU,"Smartphones").\nrun the following function on Mobile device: phone.click_close_button_popup() to click Close button for pop ups that may appear on screen.\nrun the following function on Mobile device: phone.enable_bluetooth() to enable Bluetooth for Mobile.\nrun the following function on Mobile device: phone.click_close_button_popup() to click Close button for pop ups that may appear on screen.\nextract bluetooth_device_name for HU in a variable using the following adb command: adb shell dumpsys bluetooth_manager | findstr -i "Name:".\nclick bluetooth_device_name button with regex from Mobile device display with found = phone.click_HU_bluetooth_name_button(bluetooth_device_name). This is the name of HU device we have to connect with Mobile.\nclick Cancel Button on from HU display with verification with found = click_on_device_with_verification(HU, "Cancel").\nclick Pair button from Mobile device display with verification with found = phone.click_pair_with_HU_button().\ncheck if Mobile global name word can be found on HU display with found = find_word_on_device(HU,mobile_name). If it was not found then Pairing was denied successfully by HU and the test is Passed. If it was found then Pairing denied by HU doesn\'t work properly and the test is failed.\nplease make a screenshot on Mobile device screen and save it on the path D:\\traget\\IDCevo\\IOP_configuration\\Test_results\\Screenshots. \nclick OK button from Mobile device display with phone.click_OK_button(). It may not appear everytime so we don\'t have an assert check for it.\nrun the following function on Mobile device: phone.disable_bluetooth() to disable Bluetooth of Mobile device.\nsave in Excel the status of the test (passed or failed) with the corresponding message.\nrun the following commmands after test is done in order to return to home menu: HU commands: adb shell input keyevent 3 one time; adb shell rm /sdcard/*.png; Mobile device commands: rc = phone.run_home_command(); rc = phone.run_remove_screenshot_command().\nstop screen recordings on HU and Mobile after test is done with stop_screen_recording("HU") and keep them if test is failed or delete them if test is passed.'}, {'Test Case Description': '1 Activate Bluetooth on Mobile Device.\nIn order to be visible for other Bluetooth devices you have to enter the Bluetooth settings menu of your mobile device.\n\nOn HU press COM button on ZBE or go to Communication -> Manage mobile devices -> scroll down to Manage mobile devices -> select Connect new device. -> Select function Telephone.\n2 On Mobile Device 2 select HU.\n3 Confirm pairing request and all othe requests that show up.\n', 'Test Case Expected Result': '1 HU can be found while Mobile Device 2 is searching for devices.\n2 Bluetooth pairing request screen shows up on Mobile Device 2 and HU.\nPIN code shown on both sides are the same.\n3 Mobile Device 2 is successfully paired as Hands-Free Device 2.\n\nMobile Device 1 is still paired as Hands-Free Device 1 and as Bluetooth-Audio Device.\n', 'Test Case ID': 172967, 'Test Case Precondition': 'Mobile Device 1 (Test Device) is allready paired.\nMobile Device 2 (other Device) isn`t paired with HU.', 'Test Name': 'Pairing_Mobile_Device_2', 'Test Script Description': 'check USB Matrix status with status = USB_Matrix_Status(). If USB Matrix is connected to port 1 then change it to port 2 and if is connected to any other port except port1 change the connection to port 1.\nget serial numbers for them with HU, Mobile2 = get_serial_number().\ncreate recordings folder with create_recordings_folder() and start screen recording for HU and for Mobile Device with start_screen_recording(f"-s {HU}", test_name, "HU")(example for HU).\nget Mobile device bluetooth name with adb shell settings get secure bluetooth_name.\ncreate Mobile device object with phone = create_device(Mobile2,mobile_name).\nrun the following function on Mobile device: phone.click_close_button_popup() to click Close button for pop ups that may appear on screen.\nrun the following function on Mobile device: rc = phone.run_turn_screen_on_command() to turn Mobile screen on.\nrun the following function on Mobile device: rc = phone.run_unlock_screen_command() to unlock Mobile screen.\nrun the following function on Mobile device: phone.run_settings_menu_command() go to Mobile Settings menu.\nrun the following function on Mobile device: rc = phone.run_bluetooth_menu_command() go to Mobile Bluetooth menu.\nclick Bluetooth icon from HU display with x,y = find_icon_in_screenshot(f"{path}/screenshot.png",f"{path}/helpers/Bluetooth.png") or x,y = find_icon_in_screenshot(f"{path}/screenshot.png",f"{path}/helpers/Bluetooth_2.png")\nclick Manage Devices Button from HU display with found = click_on_device(HU,"Manage devices").\nclick Smartphones Button on from HU display with found = click_on_device(HU,"Smartphones").\nclick Connect New Device Button on from HU display with found = click_on_device(HU,"Connect new device").\nrun the following function on Mobile device: phone.click_close_button_popup() to click Close button for pop ups that may appear on screen.\nrun the following function on Mobile device: phone.enable_bluetooth() to enable Bluetooth for Mobile.\nrun the following function on Mobile device: phone.click_close_button_popup() to click Close button for pop ups that may appear on screen.\nextract bluetooth_device_name for HU in a variable using the following adb command: adb shell dumpsys bluetooth_manager | findstr -i "Name:".\nclick bluetooth_device_name button with regex from Mobile device display with found = phone.click_HU_bluetooth_name_button(bluetooth_device_name). This is the name of HU device we have to connect with Mobile.\nclick Connect Button on from HU display with found = click_on_device(HU, "Connect").\nclick Pair button from Mobile device display with found = phone.click_pair_with_HU_button().\nrun the following function on Mobile Device: phone.click_allow_button_popup() in order to click Allow button for pop ups that may appear on screen.\nclick Not now button from HU display two times with found = click_on_device(HU, "Not now"). It may not appear everytime so we don\'t have an assert check for it.\ncheck if Mobile global name word can be found on HU display with found = find_word_on_device(HU, mobile_name). If it was found then second Mobile device has been connected successfully with HU and the test is Passed. If not then Mobile device name has not been found on HU Bluetooth devices list and the test is failed.\nplease make a screenshot on HU screen and save it on the path D:\\traget\\IDCevo\\IOP_configuration\\Test_results\\Screenshots. \nclick Mobile Menu Button icon from HU display with x, y = find_word_on_device_via_regex_with_coordinates(HU,mobile_name) for second Mobile device.\nclick Remove device Button with regex on from HU display with found = click_on_device_regex(HU,"Remove device") two times.\nrun the following function on Mobile device: rc = phone.run_turn_screen_on_command() to turn Mobile screen on.\nrun the following function on Mobile device: rc = phone.run_unlock_screen_command() to unlock Mobile screen.\nrun the following function on Mobile device: phone.run_settings_menu_command() go to Mobile Settings menu.\nrun the following function on Mobile device: rc = phone.run_bluetooth_menu_command() go to Mobile Bluetooth menu.\nrun the following function on Mobile device: phone.click_settings_icon() to click on Settings icon for connected Bluetooth device.\nrun the following function on Mobile device: phone.click_unpair_button() to unpair Mobile device with connected Bluetooth device.\nrun the following function on Mobile device: phone.disable_bluetooth() to disable Bluetooth of Mobile device.\nsave in Excel the status of the test (passed or failed) with the corresponding message.\nrun the following commmands after test is done in order to return to home menu: HU commands: adb shell input keyevent 3 one time; adb shell rm /sdcard/*.png; Mobile device commands: rc = phone.run_home_command().\nswitch USB Matrix back to the port from the beginning with select_mobile_device(1, status).\nstop screen recordings on HU and Mobile after test is done with stop_screen_recording("HU") and keep them if test is failed or delete them if test is passed.'}, {'Test Case Description': '1 Activate Bluetooth on Mobile Device.\nIn order to be visible for other Bluetooth devices you have to enter the Bluetooth settings menu of your mobile device.\n\nOn HU press COM button on ZBE or go to Communication -> Manage mobile devices -> scroll down to Manage mobile devices -> select Connect new device. -> Select function Telephone.\n2 On Mobile Device 1 select HU.\n3 Confirm pairing request and all other requests that show up.\n\n', 'Test Case Expected Result': '1 HU can be found while Mobile Device 1 is searching for devices.\n2 Bluetooth pairing request screen shows up on Mobile Device 1 and HU.\nPIN code shown on both sides are the same.\n3 Mobile Device 1 is successfully paired as Hands-Free Device 1 and as Bluetooth-Audio Device.\n', 'Test Case ID': 172966, 'Test Case Precondition': 'Mobile Device 1 isn`t paired with HU.\n\n', 'Test Name': 'Pairing_Mobile_Device_1', 'Test Script Description': 'check USB Matrix status with status = USB_Matrix_Status().\nget serial numbers for them with HU, Mobile1 = get_serial_number().\ncreate recordings folder with create_recordings_folder() and start screen recording for HU and for Mobile Device with start_screen_recording(f"-s {HU}", test_name, "HU")(example for HU).\nget Mobile device bluetooth name with adb shell settings get secure bluetooth_name.\ncreate Mobile device object with phone = create_device(Mobile1,mobile_name).\nrun the following function on Mobile device: phone.click_close_button_popup() to click Close button for pop ups that may appear on screen.\nrun the following function on Mobile device: rc = phone.run_turn_screen_on_command() to turn Mobile screen on.\nrun the following function on Mobile device: rc = phone.run_unlock_screen_command() to unlock Mobile screen.\nrun the following function on Mobile device: phone.run_settings_menu_command() go to Mobile Settings menu.\nrun the following function on Mobile device: rc = phone.run_bluetooth_menu_command() go to Mobile Bluetooth menu.\nclick Bluetooth icon from HU display with x,y = find_icon_in_screenshot(f"{path}/screenshot.png",f"{path}/helpers/Bluetooth.png") or x,y = find_icon_in_screenshot(f"{path}/screenshot.png",f"{path}/helpers/Bluetooth_2.png").\nclick Manage Devices Button from HU display with found = click_on_device(HU,"Manage devices").\nclick Not now Button from HU display with found = click_on_device(HU,"Not now").\nclick Smartphones Button on from HU display with found = click_on_device(HU,"Smartphones").\nrun the following function on Mobile device: phone.click_close_button_popup() to click Close button for pop ups that may appear on screen.\nrun the following function on Mobile device: phone.enable_bluetooth() to enable Bluetooth for Mobile.\nrun the following function on Mobile device: phone.click_close_button_popup() to click Close button for pop ups that may appear on screen.\nclick Cancel Button on from HU display with found = click_on_device(HU,"Cancel"). It may not appear everytime so we don\'t have an assert check for it.\nextract bluetooth_device_name for HU in a variable using the following adb command: adb shell dumpsys bluetooth_manager | findstr -i "Name:".\nclick bluetooth_device_name button with regex from Mobile device display with found = phone.click_HU_bluetooth_name_button(bluetooth_device_name). This is the name of HU device we have to connect with Mobile.\nclick Connect Button on from HU display with found = click_on_device(HU, "Connect").\nclick Pair button from Mobile device display with found = phone.click_pair_with_HU_button().\nrun the following function on Mobile Device: phone.click_allow_button_popup() in order to click Allow button for pop ups that may appear on screen.\nclick Not now button from HU display two times with found = click_on_device(HU, "Not now"). It may not appear everytime so we don\'t have an assert check for it.\nclick Smartphones Button on from HU display with found = click_on_device(HU,"Smartphones").\nclick Not now button from HU display one time with found = click_on_device(HU, "Not now"). It may not appear everytime so we don\'t have an assert check for it.\ncheck if Mobile global name word can be found on HU display with found = find_word_on_device(HU,mobile_name). If it was found then Mobile device has been connected successfully with HU and the test is Passed. If not then Mobile device name has not been found on HU Bluetooth devices list and the test is failed.\nplease make a screenshot on HU screen and save it on the path D:\\traget\\IDCevo\\IOP_configuration\\Test_results\\Screenshots. \nsave in Excel the status of the test (passed or failed) with the corresponding message.\nrun the following commmands after test is done in order to return to home menu: HU commands: adb shell input keyevent 3 one time; adb shell rm /sdcard/*.png; Mobile device commands: rc = phone.run_home_command().\nstop screen recordings on HU and Mobile after test is done with stop_screen_recording("HU") and keep them if test is failed or delete them if test is passed.'}, {'Test Case Description': 'Write down the firmware version in the Description field', 'Test Case Expected Result': 'eg. Base: M9615A-CEFWTAZM_4.0.111006\nKernel: 3.4.0\nBuild: L05E10d\n', 'Test Case ID': 172964, 'Test Case Precondition': '', 'Test Name': 'Firmware', 'Test Script Description': 'test script is located in D:\\traget\\IDCevo\\IOP_configuration\\Test_environment\\Test_scripts.\nget the serial number for HU and Mobile device with HU, Mobile1 = get_serial_number().\nrun the following command: dir D:\\ /s /b | findstr /r "traget.*IDCevo.*[0-9][0-9]w[0-9]*\\.[0-9]*-[0-9].*images.*idcevo-hv.*Flashbins.*IDCEvo-Artifacts.*tools.*fastboot$".\nrun the following adb command on HU: adb shell getprop ro.build.fingerprint.\ncheck if adb command returns the Firmware of the HU. If it returns the Firmware then the test is Passed. If not then test is Failed.\nsave in Excel the status of the test (passed or failed) with the corresponding message.'}, {'Test Case Description': 'Write down the OS version in the Description field', 'Test Case Expected Result': 'eg. 7.1', 'Test Case ID': 172963, 'Test Case Precondition': '', 'Test Name': 'OS_version', 'Test Script Description': 'test script is located in D:\\traget\\IDCevo\\IOP_configuration\\Test_environment\\Test_scripts.\nget the serial number for HU and Mobile device with HU, Mobile1 = get_serial_number().\nrun the following adb command on HU: adb shell getprop ro.build.version.release.\ncheck if adb command returns Android version. If it returns Android version then the test is Passed. If not then test is Failed.\nsave in Excel the status of the test (passed or failed) with the corresponding message.'}, {'Test Case Description': 'Write down the OS in the Description field ', 'Test Case Expected Result': 'eg. Android', 'Test Case ID': 172962, 'Test Case Precondition': '', 'Test Name': 'OS', 'Test Script Description': 'test script is located in D:\\traget\\IDCevo\\IOP_configuration\\Test_environment\\Test_scripts.\nget the serial number for HU and Mobile device with HU, Mobile1 = get_serial_number().\nrun the following command: dir D:\\ /s /b | findstr /r "traget.*IDCevo.*[0-9][0-9]w[0-9]*\\.[0-9]*-[0-9].*images.*idcevo-hv.*Flashbins.*IDCEvo-Artifacts.*tools.*fastboot$".\nrun the following adb command on HU: adb shell "if [ -f /system/build.prop ] || [ -f /vendor/build.prop ]; then echo Android; else echo Unknown; fi".\ncheck if adb command returns Android. If it returns Android then the test is Passed. If not then test is Failed.\nsave in Excel the status of the test (passed or failed) with the corresponding message.'}]}
