e(HU,"Smartphones").\nrun the following function on Mobile device: phone.click_close_button_popup() to click Close button for pop ups that may appear on screen.\nrun the following function on Mobile device: phone.enable_bluetooth() to enable Bluetooth for Mobile.\nrun the following function on Mobile device: phone.click_close_button_popup() to click Close button for pop ups that may appear on screen.\nclick Cancel Button on from HU display with found = click_on_device(HU,"Cancel"). It may not appear everytime so we don\'t have an assert check for it.\nextract bluetooth_device_name for HU in a variable using the following adb command: adb shell dumpsys bluetooth_manager | findstr -i "Name:".\nclick bluetooth_device_name button with regex from Mobile device display with found = phone.click_HU_bluetooth_name_button(bluetooth_device_name). This is the name of HU device we have to connect with Mobile.\nclick Connect Button on from HU display with found = click_on_device(HU, "Connect").\nclick Pair button from Mobile device display with found = phone.click_pair_with_HU_button().\nrun the following function on Mobile Device: phone.click_allow_button_popup() in order to click Allow button for pop ups that may appear on screen.\nclick Not now button from HU display two times with found = click_on_device(HU, "Not now"). It may not appear everytime so we don\'t have an assert check for it.\nclick Smartphones Button on from HU display with found = click_on_device(HU,"Smartphones").\nclick Not now button from HU display one time with found = click_on_device(HU, "Not now"). It may not appear everytime so we don\'t have an assert check for it.\ncheck if Mobile global name word can be found on HU display with found = find_word_on_device(HU,mobile_name). If it was found then Mobile device has been connected successfully with HU and the test is Passed. If not then Mobile device name has not been found on HU Bluetooth devices list and the test is failed.\nplease make a screenshot on H