ith regex from HU display with found = click_on_device_regex(HU, mobile_name).\nrun the following adb command on HU display: adb shell input swipe 1700 700 200 2500.\nsave in Excel the status of the test (passed or failed) with the corresponding message.\nrun the following commmands after test is done in order to return to home menu: HU commands: adb shell input keyevent 3 one time; adb shell rm /sdcard/*.png.\nstop screen recordings on HU and Mobile after test is done with stop_screen_recording("HU") and keep them if test is failed or delete them if test is passed.'}, {'Test Case Description': '1 Go to Communications --> Contacts\n2 Go to a contact that has blanks in its contact details.\n', 'Test Case Expected Result': '2 Blanks are displayed correctly.', 'Test Case ID': 172987, 'Test Case Precondition': 'Mobile Device and HU are connected.\nPhonebook download is finished.\nA contact with blanks (some spaces between charakters) in contact details is stored in Phonebook.', 'Test Name': 'Blanks_in_contact_details', 'Test Script Description': 'check USB Matrix status with status = USB_Matrix_Status().\nget serial numbers for them with HU, Mobile1 = get_serial_number().\ncreate recordings folder with create_recordings_folder() and start screen recording for HU with start_screen_recording(f"-s {HU}", test_name, "HU")(example for HU).\nget Mobile device bluetooth name with adb shell settings get secure bluetooth_name.\ncreate Mobile device object with phone = create_device(Mobile1,mobile_name).\nclick Mobile device name button with regex from HU display with found = click_on_device_regex(HU, mobile_name).\nclick Contacts Button on from HU display with found = click_on_device(HU, "Contacts").\nrun the following function on mobile device: stdout = phone.get_contacts_name_command(). Extract the display_name for all contacts displayed in a list.\nrun the following function on mobile device: stdout = phone.get_contacts_name_with_postal_address_command(). Extract the display_