ult': '2 All special characters displayed correctly.', 'Test Case ID': 172986, 'Test Case Precondition': 'Mobile Device and HU are connected.\nPhonebook download is finished.\nPhonebook has contacts with special characters (e.g.: &, $,%, §, ä, ü, ö)', 'Test Name': 'Special_characters', 'Test Script Description': 'check USB Matrix status with status = USB_Matrix_Status().\nget serial numbers for them with HU, Mobile1 = get_serial_number().\ncreate recordings folder with create_recordings_folder() and start screen recording for HU with start_screen_recording(f"-s {HU}", test_name, "HU")(example for HU).\nget Mobile device bluetooth name with adb shell settings get secure bluetooth_name.\ncreate Mobile device object with phone = create_device(Mobile1,mobile_name).\nclick Mobile device name button with regex from HU display with found = click_on_device_regex(HU, mobile_name).\nclick Contacts Button on from HU display with found = click_on_device(HU, "Contacts").\nrun the following function on mobile device: stdout = phone.get_contacts_name_command().\nextract the first contact for which contains special charaters in the name. Check if the contact last name is available with stdout = phone.get_contacts_data3_command() and if it is save it in a variable. If not save the whole name in a variable with stdout = phone.get_contacts_data2_command().\nclick on the extracted name Button on from HU display with found = click_on_device_with_verification(HU, click_target). If it was not found run the following adb command: adb shell input swipe 1700 700 2000 200 to scroll down on contacts list from HU display. Try it for 10 times if the extracted contact was not found the test is failed.\ncheck if special characters from the name word can be found on HU display with regex with special_chars_in_name = special_chars_pattern.findall(click_target). If it was found then Mobile device Contact with special characters is displayed successfully on HU and the test is Passed. If not then Mobile device Contact with special characters is not displayed and the test is failed.\nplease make a screenshot on HU screen and save it on the path D:\\traget\\IDCevo\\IOP_configuration\\Test_results\\Screenshots.\nrun the following adb command on HU: adb shell input keyevent 3.\nclick Mobile device name button with regex from HU display with found = click_on_device_regex(HU, mobile_name).\nrun the following adb command on HU display: adb shell input swipe 1700 700 200 2500.\nsave in Excel the status of the test (passed or failed) with the corresponding message.\nrun the following commmands after test is done in order to return to home menu: HU commands: adb shell input keyevent 3 one time; adb shell rm /sdcard/*.png.\nstop screen recordings on HU and Mobile after test is done with stop_screen_recording("HU") and keep them if test is failed or delete them if test is passed.'}, {'Test Case Description': '1 Go to Communication --> Contacts\n2 CheIDCEvo if pictures are displayed correctly.\n', 'Test Case Expected Result': '2 Contact picture of contacts are displayed correctly.', 'Test Case ID': 172985, 'Test Case Precondition': 'Mobile Device and HU are connected.\nPhonebook download is finished.\nSync animation can`t be seen anymore.\nContactbook has contacs with picture.', 'Test Name': 'Contact_picture', 'Test Script Description': 'check USB Matrix status with status = USB_Matrix_Status().\nget serial numbers for them with HU, Mobile1 = get_serial_number().\ncreate recordings folder with create_recordings_folder() and start screen recording for HU with start_screen_recording(f"-s {HU}", test_name, "HU")(example for HU).\nget Mobile device bluetooth name with adb shell settings get secure bluetooth_name.\ncreate Mobile device object with phone = create_device(Mobile1,mobile_name).\nclick Mobile device name button with regex from HU display with found = click_on_device_regex(HU, mobile_name).\nclick Contacts Button on from HU display with found = click_on_device(HU, "Contacts").\nrun the following function on mobile device: stdout = phone.get_contacts_name_and_photo_id_command().\nextract the first contact for which the photo_id is not NULL and positive. Check if the contact last name is available with stdout = phone.get_contacts_data3_command() and if it is save it in a variable. If not save the whole name in a variable with stdout = phone.get_contacts_data2_command().\nclick on the extracted name Button on from HU display with found = click_on_device_regex(HU, click_target) or found = click_on_device_with_verification(HU, click_target). If it was not found run the following adb command: adb shell input swipe 1700 700 2000 200 to scroll down on contacts list from HU display. Try it for 10 times if the extracted contact was not found the test is failed.\nrun the following function on mobile device: stdout = phone.check_contacts_photo_data_command(contact_id).\ncheck if data15=BLOB word can be found in the command response with regex. If it was found then Mobile device Contact Picture is displayed successfully on HU and the test is Passed. If not then Mobile device Contact Picture is not displayed and the test is failed.\nplease make a screenshot on HU screen and save it on the path D:\\traget\\IDCevo\\IOP_configuration\\Test_results\\Screenshots.\nrun the following adb command on HU: adb shell input keyevent 3.\nclick Mobile device name button with regex from HU display with found = click_on_device_regex(HU, mobile_name).\nrun the following adb command on HU display: adb shell input swipe 1700 700 200 2500.\nsave in Excel the status of the test (passed or failed) with the corresponding message.\nrun the following commmands after test is done in order to return to home menu: HU commands: adb shell input keyevent 3 one time; adb shell rm /sdcard/*.png.\nstop screen recordings on HU and Mobile after test is done with stop_screen_recording("HU") and keep them if test is failed or delete them if test is passed.'}, {'Test Case Description': '1 While phonebook is downloading start audio playbaIDCEvo from Mobile Device.', 'Test Case Expected Result': '1 Audio playbaIDCEvo does not interrupt phonebook download.', 'Test Case ID': 172984, 'Test Case Precondition': 'Mobile Device and HU are connected.\nPhonebook download has started and is not finished.\nIn case the download of the phonebook is already finished, then delete Mobile Device on HU', 'Test Name': 'Audio_playback_during_phonebook_download', 'Test Script Description': 'check USB Matrix status with status = USB_Matrix_Status().\nget serial numbers for them with HU, Mobile1 = get_serial_number().\ncreate recordings folder with create_recordings_folder() and start screen recording for HU and for Mobile Device with start_screen_recording(f"-s {HU}", test_name, "HU")(example for HU).\nget Mobile device bluetooth name with adb shell settings get secure bluetooth_name.\ncreate Mobile device object with phone = create_device(Mobile1,mobile_name).\nrun the following function on Mobile device: phone.click_close_button_popup() to click Close button for pop ups that may appear on screen.\nrun the following function on Mobile device: rc = phone.run_turn_screen_on_command() to turn Mobile screen on.\nrun the following function on Mobile device: rc = phone.run_unlock_screen_command() to unlock Mobile screen.\nrun the following function on Mobile device: phone.run_settings_menu_command() go to Mobile Settings menu.\nrun the following function on Mobile device: rc = phone.run_bluetooth_menu_command() go to Mobile Bluetooth menu.\nclick Bluetooth icon from HU display with x,y = find_icon_in_screenshot(f"{path}/screenshot.png",f"{path}/helpers/Bluetooth.png") or x,y = find_icon_in_screenshot(f"{path}/screenshot.png",f"{path}/helpers/Bluetooth_2.png")\nclick Manage Devices Button from HU display with found = click_on_device(HU,"Manage devices").\nclick Not now Button from HU display with found = click_on_device(HU,"Not now").\nclick Smartphones Button on from HU display with found = click_on_device(HU,"Smartphones").\nrun the following function on Mobile device: phone.click_close_button_popup() to click Close button for pop ups that may appear on screen.\nrun the following function on Mobile device: phone.enable_bluetooth() to enable Bluetooth for Mobile.\nrun the following function on Mobile device: phone.click_close_button_popup() to click Close button for pop ups that may appear on screen.\nextract bluetooth_device_name for HU in a variable using the following adb command: adb shell dumpsys bluetooth_manager | findstr -i "Name:".\nclick bluetooth_device_name button with regex from Mobile device display with found = phone.click_HU_bluetooth_name_button(bluetooth_device_name). This is the name of HU device we have to connect with Mobile.\nclick Connect Button on from HU display with found = click_on_device(HU, "Connect").\nclick Pair button from Mobile device display with found = phone.click_pair_with_HU_button().\nclick Not now button from HU display with found = click_on_device(HU, "Not now"). It may not appear everytime so we don\'t have an assert check for it.\nrun the following function on Mobile device: phone.play_audio_command()to play audio.\nrun the following adb command on HU: adb shell input keyevent 3 to go to Home screen.\nclick Not now button from HU display with found = click_on_device(HU, "Not now"). It may not appear everytime so we don\'t have an assert check for it.\nclick Mobile device name button with regex from HU display with found = click_on_device_regex(HU, mobile_name).\nclick Contacts Button on from HU display with found = click_on_device(HU, "Contacts").\ncheck if Contacts word can be found on HU display with regex with found = find_word_on_device_via_regex(HU, "Contacts"). If it was found then Mobile device Phonebook is downloading during audio playback and the test is Passed. If not then Mobile device Phonebook download failed during audio playback and the test is failed.\nplease make a screenshot on HU screen and save it on the path D:\\traget\\IDCevo\\IOP_configuration\\Test_results\\Screenshots.\nrun the following function on Mobile Device: phone.click_allow_button_popup() in order to click Allow button for pop ups that may appear on screen.\nrun the following function on Mobile Device: phone.pause_audio_command() to pause audio.\nclick Bluetooth icon from HU display with x,y = find_icon_in_screenshot(f"{path}/screenshot.png",f"{path}/helpers/Bluetooth.png") or x,y = find_icon_in_screenshot(f"{path}/screenshot.png",f"{path}/helpers/Bluetooth_2.png")\nclick Manage Devices Button from HU display with found = click_on_device(HU,"Manage devices").\nclick Smartphones Button on from HU display with found = click_on_device(HU,"Smartphones").\nclick Mobile Menu Button icon from HU display with x,y = find_icon_in_screenshot(f"{path}/screenshot.png",f"{path}/helpers/Mobile_Menu_Button.png") or x,y = find_icon_in_screenshot(f"{path}/screenshot.png",f"{path}/helpers/Mobile_Menu_Button_2.png")\nclick Remove device Button with regex on from HU display with found = click_on_device_regex(HU,"Remove device").\nrun the following function on Mobile device: rc = phone.run_turn_screen_on_command() to turn Mobile screen on.\nrun the following function on Mobile device: rc = phone.run_unlock_screen_command() to unlock Mobile screen.\nrun the following function on Mobile device: phone.run_settings_menu_command() go to Mobile Settings menu.\nrun the following function on Mobile device: rc = phone.run_bluetooth_menu_command() go to Mobile Bluetooth menu.\nrun the following function on Mobile device: phone.click_settings_icon() to click on Settings icon for connected Bluetooth device.\nrun the following function on Mobile device: phone.click_unpair_button() to unpair Mobile device with connected Bluetooth device.\nrun the following function on Mobile device: phone.disable_bluetooth() to disable Bluetooth of Mobile device.\nsave in Excel the status of the test (passed, failed or skipped) with the corresponding message.\nrun the following commmands after test is done in order to return to home menu: HU commands: adb shell input keyevent 3 one time; adb shell rm /sdcard/*.png; Mobile device commands: rc = phone.run_home_command()\nstop screen recordings on HU and Mobile device after test is done with stop_screen_recording("HU") and keep them if test is failed or delete them if test is passed.'}, {'Test Case Description': '1 Phonebook download is initiated and still running. Use a shielding bag or shielding chamber or go out of range to simulate a linkloss', 'Test Case Expected Result': '1 After linkloss HU and Mobile Device cancel import and return to previous states.', 'Test Case ID': 172983, 'Test Case Precondition': 'Mobile Device and HU are connected.\nPhonebook download has started and is not finished.\nIn case the download of the phonebook is already finished, then delete Mobile Device on HU', 'Test Name': 'Linkloss_during_phonebook_download', 'Test Script Description': 'check USB Matrix status with status = USB_Matrix_Status().\nget serial numbers for them with HU, Mobile1 = get_serial_number().\ncreate recordings folder with create_recordings_folder() and start screen recording for HU and for Mobile Device with start_screen_recording(f"-s {HU}", test_name, "HU")(example for HU).\nget Mobile device bluetooth name with adb shell settings get secure bluetooth_name.\ncreate Mobile device object with phone = create_device(Mobile1,mobile_name).\nrun the following function on Mobile device: phone.click_close_button_popup() to click Close button for pop ups that may appear on screen.\nrun the following function on Mobile device: rc = phone.run_turn_screen_on_command() to turn Mobile screen on.\nrun the following function on Mobile device: rc = phone.run_unlock_screen_command() to unlock Mobile screen.\nrun the following function on Mobile device: phone.run_settings_menu_command() go to Mobile Settings menu.\nrun the following function on Mobile device: rc = phone.run_bluetooth_menu_command() go to Mobile Bluetooth menu.\nclick Bluetooth icon from HU display with x,y = find_icon_in_screenshot(f"{path}/screenshot.png",f"{path}/helpers/Bluetooth.png") or x,y = find_icon_in_screenshot(f"{path}/screenshot.png",f"{path}/helpers/Bluetooth_2.png")\nclick Manage Devices Button from HU display with found = click_on_device(HU,"Manage devices").\nclick Not now Button from HU display with found = click_on_device(HU,"Not now").\nclick Smartphones Button on from HU display with found = click_on_device(HU,"Smartphones").\nrun the following function on Mobile device: phone.click_close_button_popup() to click Close button for pop ups that may appear on screen.\nrun the following function on Mobile device: phone.enable_bluetooth() to enable Bluetooth for Mobile.\nrun the following function on Mobile device: phone.click_close_button_popup() to click Close button for pop ups that may appear on screen.\nextract bluetooth_device_name for HU in a variable using the following adb command: adb shell dumpsys bluetooth_manager | findstr -i "Name:".\nclick bluetooth_device_name button with regex from Mobile device display with found = phone.click_HU_bluetooth_name_button(bluetooth_device_name). This is the name of HU device we have to connect with Mobile.\nclick Connect Button on from HU display with found = click_on_device(HU, "Connect").\nclick Pair button from Mobile device display with found = phone.click_pair_with_HU_button().\nclick Not now button from HU display with found = click_on_device(HU, "Not now"). It may not appear everytime so we don\'t have an assert check for it.\nrun the following adb command on HU: adb shell input keyevent 3 to go to HU home screen.\nclick Not now button from HU display with found = click_on_device(HU, "Not now"). It may not appear everytime so we don\'t have an assert check for it.\nclick Mobile device name button with regex from HU display with found = click_on_device_regex(HU, mobile_name).\nclick Contacts Button on from HU display with found = click_on_device(HU, "Contacts").\nrun the following function on Mobile device: phone.run_linkloss_command(). Wait 15 seconds.\nclick Not now button from HU display one time with found = click_on_device(HU, "Not now"). It may not appear everytime so we don\'t have an assert check for it.\ncheck if Contacts word can be found on HU display with regex with found = find_word_on_device_via_regex(HU, "Contacts"). If it was found then Mobile device Phonebook is resuming download after Linkloss and the test is Passed. If not then Mobile device Phonebook download failed after Linkloss and the test is failed.\nplease make a screenshot on HU screen and save it on the path D:\\traget\\IDCevo\\IOP_configuration\\Test_results\\Screenshots.\nrun the following function on Mobile Device: phone.click_allow_button_popup() in order to click Allow button for pop ups that may appear on screen.\nclick Bluetooth icon from HU display with x,y = find_icon_in_screenshot(f"{path}/screenshot.png",f"{path}/helpers/Bluetooth.png") or x,y = find_icon_in_screenshot(f"{path}/screenshot.png",f"{path}/helpers/Bluetooth_2.png")\nclick Manage Devices Button from HU display with found = click_on_device(HU,"Manage devices").\nclick Smartphones Button on from HU display with found = click_on_device(HU,"Smartphones").\nclick Mobile Menu Button icon from HU display with x,y = find_icon_in_screenshot(f"{path}/screenshot.png",f"{path}/helpers/Mobile_Menu_Button.png") or x,y = find_icon_in_screenshot(f"{path}/screenshot.png",f"{path}/helpers/Mobile_Menu_Button_2.png")\nclick Remove device Button with regex on from HU display with found = click_on_device_regex(HU,"Remove device").\nrun the following function on Mobile device: rc = phone.run_turn_screen_on_command() to turn Mobile screen on.\nrun the following function on Mobile device: rc = phone.run_unlock_screen_command() to unlock Mobile screen.\nrun the following function on Mobile device: phone.run_settings_menu_command() go to Mobile Settings menu.\nrun the following function on Mobile device: rc = phone.run_bluetooth_menu_command() go to Mobile Bluetooth menu.\nrun the following function on Mobile device: phone.click_settings_icon() to click on Settings icon for connected Bluetooth device.\nrun the following function on Mobile device: phone.click_unpair_button() to unpair Mobile device with connected Bluetooth device.\nrun the following function on Mobile device: phone.disable_bluetooth() to disable Bluetooth of Mobile device.\nsave in Excel the status of the test (passed, failed or skipped) with the corresponding message.\nrun the following commmands after test is done in order to return to home menu: HU commands: adb shell input keyevent 3 one time; adb shell rm /sdcard/*.png; Mobile device commands: rc = phone.run_home_command()\nstop screen recordings on HU and Mobile device after test is done with stop_screen_recording("HU") and keep them if test is failed or delete them if test is passed.'}, {'Test Case Description': '1 Initiate call from Mobile Device 1 (paired Mobile Device) to Mobile Device 3 during phonebook download.', 'Test Case Expected Result': '1 Outgoing call does not interrupt phonebook download.', 'Test Case ID': 172982, 'Test Case Precondition': 'Mobile Device and HU are connected.\nPhonebook download has started and is not finished.\nIn case the download of the phonebook is already finished, then delete Mobile Device on HU', 'Test Name': 'Outgoing_call_during_phonebook_download', 'Test Script Description': 'check USB Matrix status with status = USB_Matrix_Status().\nget serial numbers for them with HU, Mobile1 = get_serial_number().\nget Mobile device bluetooth name with adb shell settings get secure bluetooth_name.\ncreate Mobile device object with phone = create_device(Mobile1,mobile_name).\nrun the following function on Mobile device: sim_state = phone.check_SIM_command(). If the command does not contain word LOADED Mobile device doesn\'t have SIM card on it and test is skipped.\nextract the mobile1 phone number with phone_number_mobile1 = phone.get_phone_number_command().\ncheck USB Matrix status with status = USB_Matrix_Status(). If USB Matrix is connected to port 1 then change it to port 2 and if is connected to any other port except port1 change the connection to port 1.\nget serial numbers for them with HU, Mobile2 = get_serial_number().\nget Mobile device bluetooth name with adb shell settings get secure bluetooth_name.\ncreate Mobile device2 object with phone = create_device(Mobile2,mobile_name).\nrun the following function on Mobile device: sim_state = phone2.check_SIM_command(). If the command does not contain word LOADED Mobile device doesn\'t have SIM card on it and test is skipped.\nextract the mobile2 phone number with phone_number_mobile2 = phone2.get_phone_number_command().\nswitch USB Matrix back to the port from the beginning with select_mobile_device(1, status).\nrun the following function on Mobile device: rc = phone.run_turn_screen_on_command() to turn screen on.\nrun the following function on Mobile device: rc = phone.run_unlock_screen_command() to unlock screen.\nrun the following function on Mobile device: rc = phone.dial_command(phone_number_mobile2) to initiate a call on Mobile2.\ncheck USB Matrix status with status = USB_Matrix_Status(). If USB Matrix is connected to port 1 then change it to port 2 and if is connected to any other port except port1 change the connection to port 1.\nrun the following function on Mobile device2: rc = phone2.answer_call_command() to accept the call from Mobile1.\nswitch USB Matrix back to the port from the beginning with select_mobile_device(1, status).\nget Mobile device bluetooth name with adb shell settings get secure bluetooth_name.\ncreate recordings folder with create_recordings_folder() and start screen recording for HU and for Mobile Device with start_screen_recording(f"-s {HU}", test_name, "HU")(example for HU).\nrun the following functi