 adb pull /data/misc/bluetooth/logs/btsnoop_hci.log.last btsnoop_hci_before_poweroff_active.log.last; move btsnoop* D:/traget/IDCevo/IOP_configuration/Test_results in order to extract BTsnoop logs from HU before power off.\nrun the following function: power_off_HU() on HU to power off HU during active call.Wait 10 seconds for HU to completely power off.\nrun the following function on Mobile device: rc = phone.run_turn_screen_on_command() to turn Mobile screen on.\nrun the following function on Mobile device: rc = phone.run_unlock_screen_command() to unlock Mobile screen.\nrun the following function on Mobile device: phone.run_settings_menu_command() go to Mobile Settings menu.\nrun the following function on Mobile device: rc = phone.run_bluetooth_menu_command() go to Mobile Bluetooth menu.\ncheck if bluetooth connection was released after HU power off with found = phone.check_bluetooth_connection(). If found contains the following text: ConnectionState: STATE_DISCONNECTED then Bluetooth connection was released and call is transferred to Mobile Device 1 and the test is Passed. If not then call was terminated or connection remained active and the test is Failed.\nplease make a screenshot on Mobile device screen and save it on the path D:\\traget\\IDCevo\\IOP_configuration\\Test_results\\Screenshots.\nrun the following function to power on HU: power_on_HU() during incoming call. Wait 60 seconds for HU to boot up and establish Bluetooth connection.\nrun the following command in Windows cmd to resume DLT logs after reboot: ssh -i id_ed25519_idcevo -o StrictHostKeyChecking=no -o ConnectTimeout=10 root@160.48.249.99 "nohup dlt-receive -a localhost -o /var/data/{mobile_name_without_space}.dlt >/dev/null 2>&1 &".\nclick Retry icon button from PC display with click_on_Retry(). Wait 30 seconds for HU to initialize properly.\nget serial numbers for them with HU, Mobile1 = get_serial_number().\nclick X icon from HU display 2 times with x, y = find_icon_in_screenshot(f"{path}/scr