es then correct field strength is shown on HU and the test is Passed. If not then field strength indication is incorrect and the test is failed.\nplease make a screenshot on HU screen and save it on the path D:\\\\traget\\\\IDCevo\\\\IOP_configuration\\\\Test_results\\\\Screenshots.\nsave in Excel the status of the test (passed or failed) with the corresponding message.\nrun the following commands after test is done in order to return to home menu: HU commands: adb shell input keyevent 3 one time; adb shell rm /sdcard/*.png; Mobile device commands: rc = phone.run_home_command().\nstop screen recordings on HU after test is done with stop_screen_recording("HU") and keep them if test is failed or delete them if test is passed.'}, {'Test Case Description': '1 Initiate a call from Mobile Device 3 to Mobile Device 1.\n2 Accept call from Mobile Device 3 on HU.\n3 Initiate a call from Mobile Device 4 to Mobile Device 1.\n4 Accept call from Mobile Device 4 on HU.\nIDCEvo:\n5 Navigate to Conference Call and establish conference call.\nMGU22:\n5 Press Conference Call from Mobile Device 1 to establish conference call.', 'Test Case Expected Result': '1 1st call from Mobile Device 3 is on hold. 2nd call from Mobile Device 4 active. \n2 After the merge conference call is active, both incoming calls from Mobile Device 3 and Mobile Device 4 are audible on HU.', 'Test Case ID': 173023, 'Test Case Precondition': 'Mobile Device 1 and HU are connected.\nSynchronisation is finished.', 'Test Name': 'Conference_call', 'Test Script Description': 'check USB Matrix status with status = USB_Matrix_Status().\nget serial numbers for them with HU, Mobile1 = get_serial_number().\nget Mobile device bluetooth name with adb shell settings get secure bluetooth_name.\ncreate recordings folder with create_recordings_folder() and start screen recording for HU with start_screen_recording(f"-s {HU}", test_name, "HU")(example for HU).\ncreate Mobile device object with phone = create_device(Mobile1,mobile_name).\nrun the following function on Mobile device: sim_state = phone.check_SIM_command(). If the command does not contain word LOADED Mobile device doesn\'t have SIM card on it and test is skipped.\nextract the mobile1 phone number with phone_number_mobile1 = phone.get_phone_number_command().\nclick Mobile device name button with regex from HU display with found = click_on_device_regex(HU, mobile_name).\nclick Contacts Button on from HU display with found = click_on_device(HU, "Contacts").\ncheck USB Matrix status with status = USB_Matrix_Status(). If USB Matrix is connected to port 1 then change it to port 2 and if is connected to any other port except port1 change the connection to port 1.\nget serial numbers for them with HU, Mobile3 = get_serial_number().\nget Mobile device bluetooth name with adb shell settings get secure bluetooth_name.\ncreate Mobile device3 object with phone3 = create_device(Mobile3,mobile_name3).\nrun the following function on Mobile device: sim_state = phone3.check_SIM_command(). If the command does not contain word LOADED Mobile device doesn\'t have SIM card on it and test is skipped.\nextract the mobile3 phone number with phone_number_mobile3 = phone3.get_phone_number_command().\nrun the following function on Mobile device3: rc = phone3.run_turn_screen_on_command() to turn Mobile3 screen on.\nrun the following function on Mobile device3: rc = phone3.run_unlock_screen_command() to unlock Mobile3 screen.\nrun the following function on Mobile device3: rc = phone3.dial_command(phone_number_mobile1) to initiate a call from Mobile Device 3 to Mobile Device 1. Wait 5 seconds for the call to be established.\nclick Accept button with regex from HU display with found = click_on_device_regex(HU, "Accept") to accept call from Mobile Device 3 on HU.\nswitch USB Matrix back to the port from the beginning with select_mobile_device(1, status).\ncheck USB Matrix status with status = USB_Matrix_Status(). If USB Matrix is connected to port 1 or 2 then change it to port 3 and if is connected to any other port except port1 or port 2 change the connection to port 2.\nget serial numbers for them with HU, Mobile4 = get_serial_number().\nget Mobile device bluetooth name with adb shell settings get secure bluetooth_name.\ncreate Mobile device4 object with phone4 = create_device(Mobile4,mobile_name4).\nrun the following function on Mobile device: sim_state = phone4.check_SIM_command(). If the command does not contain word LOADED Mobile device doesn\'t have SIM card on it and test is skipped.\nextract the mobile4 phone number with phone_number_mobile4 = phone4.get_phone_number_command().\nrun the following function on Mobile device4: rc = phone4.run_turn_screen_on_command() to turn Mobile4 screen on.\nrun the following function on Mobile device4: rc = phone4.run_unlock_screen_command() to unlock Mobile4 screen.\nrun the following function on Mobile device4: rc = phone4.dial_command(phone_number_mobile1) to initiate a call from Mobile Device 4 to Mobile Device 1. Wait 5 seconds for the second call to be established.\nclick Accept button with regex from HU display with found = click_on_device_regex(HU, "Accept") to accept call from Mobile Device 4 on HU.\nswitch USB Matrix back to the port from the beginning with select_mobile_device(1, status).\nclick Conference Call button with regex from HU display with found = click_on_device_regex(HU, "Conference") to navigate to Conference Call and establish conference call.\ncheck if last 3 digits of mobile3 and mobile4 phone numbers can be found on HU display with found = find_word_on_device_via_regex(HU, last_3_digits_mobile3) and found = find_word_on_device_via_regex(HU, last_3_digits_mobile4). If both were found then 1st call from Mobile Device 3 is on hold, 2nd call from Mobile Device 4 active, and after the merge conference call is active with both incoming calls from Mobile Device 3 and Mobile Device 4 audible on HU and the test is Passed. If not then conference call functionality is not working properly and the test is failed.\nplease make a screenshot on HU screen and save it on the path D:\\traget\\IDCevo\\IOP_configuration\\Test_results\\Screenshots.\nrun the following function on Mobile Device1: phone.end_call_command() in order to end call.\nsave in Excel the status of the test (passed, failed or skipped) with the corresponding message.\nrun the following commands after test is done in order to return to home menu: HU commands: adb shell input keyevent 3 one time; adb shell rm /sdcard/*.png; Mobile device commands: rc = phone.run_home_command().\nstop screen recordings on HU after test is done with stop_screen_recording("HU") and keep them if test is failed or delete them if test is passed.'}, {'Test Case Description': '1 Initiate a call from Mobile Device 3 to Mobile Device 1.\n2 Accept call from Mobile Device 3 on HU.\n3 Initiate a call from Mobile Device 4 to Mobile Device 1.\n4 Accept call from Mobile Device 4 on HU.\n5 Switch between both calls a few times.', 'Test Case Expected Result': '4 1st call from Mobile Device 3 is on hold. 2nd call from Mobile Device 4 active. \n5 1st call from Mobile Device 3 is active. 2nd call from Mobile Device 4 is on hold.', 'Test Case ID': 173022, 'Test Case Precondition': 'Mobile Device and HU are connected.\nSynchronisation is finished.', 'Test Name': 'Multiparty_call_switching', 'Test Script Description': '\ncheck USB Matrix status with status = USB_Matrix_Status().\nget serial numbers for them with HU, Mobile1 = get_serial_number().\nget Mobile device bluetooth name with adb shell settings get secure bluetooth_name.\ncreate recordings folder with create_recordings_folder() and start screen recording for HU with start_screen_recording(f"-s {HU}", test_name, "HU")(example for HU).\ncreate Mobile device object with phone = create_device(Mobile1,mobile_name).\nrun the following function on Mobile device: sim_state = phone.check_SIM_command(). If the command does not contain word LOADED Mobile device doesn\'t have SIM card on it and test is skipped.\nextract the mobile1 phone number with phone_number_mobile1 = phone.get_phone_number_command().\nclick Mobile device name button with regex from HU display with found = click_on_device_regex(HU, mobile_name).\nclick Contacts Button on from HU display with found = click_on_device(HU, "Contacts").\ncheck USB Matrix status with status = USB_Matrix_Status(). If USB Matrix is connected to port 1 then change it to port 2 and if is connected to any other port except port1 change the connection to port 1.\nget serial numbers for them with HU, Mobile3 = get_serial_number().\nget Mobile device bluetooth name with adb shell settings get secure bluetooth_name.\ncreate Mobile device3 object with phone3 = create_device(Mobile3,mobile_name3).\nrun the following function on Mobile device: sim_state = phone3.check_SIM_command(). If the command does not contain word LOADED Mobile device doesn\'t have SIM card on it and test is skipped.\nextract the mobile3 phone number with phone_number_mobile3 = phone3.get_phone_number_command().\nrun the following function on Mobile device3: rc = phone3.run_turn_screen_on_command() to turn Mobile3 screen on.\nrun the following function on Mobile device3: rc = phone3.run_unlock_screen_command() to unlock Mobile3 screen.\nrun the following function on Mobile device3: rc = phone3.dial_command(phone_number_mobile1) to initiate a call from Mobile Device 3 to Mobile Device 1. Wait 5 seconds for the call to be established.\nclick Accept button with regex from HU display with found = click_on_device_regex(HU, "Accept") to accept call from Mobile Device 3 on HU.\nswitch USB Matrix back to the port from the beginning with select_mobile_device(1, status).\nwait 3 seconds for the first call to become active.\ncheck USB Matrix status with status = USB_Matrix_Status(). If USB Matrix is connected to port 1 or 2 then change it to port 3 and if is connected to any other port except port1 or port 2 change the connection to port 2.\nget serial numbers for them with HU, Mobile4 = get_serial_number().\nget Mobile device bluetooth name with adb shell settings get secure bluetooth_name.\ncreate Mobile device4 object with phone4 = create_device(Mobile4,mobile_name4).\nrun the following function on Mobile device: sim_state = phone4.check_SIM_command(). If the command does not contain word LOADED Mobile device doesn\'t have SIM card on it and test is skipped.\nextract the mobile4 phone number with phone_number_mobile4 = phone4.get_phone_number_command().\nrun the following function on Mobile device4: rc = phone4.run_turn_screen_on_command() to turn Mobile4 screen on.\nrun the following function on Mobile device4: rc = phone4.run_unlock_screen_command() to unlock Mobile4 screen.\nrun the following function on Mobile device4: rc = phone4.dial_command(phone_number_mobile1) to initiate a call from Mobile Device 4 to Mobile Device 1. Wait 5 seconds for the second call to be established.\nswitch USB Matrix back to the port from the beginning with select_mobile_device(1, status).\nclick Accept button with regex from HU display with found = click_on_device_regex(HU, "Accept") to accept call from Mobile Device 4 on HU.\nwait 3 seconds for call switching to take effect.\ncheck if last 3 digits of mobile4 phone number can be found on HU display with found = find_word_on_device_via_regex(HU, last_3_digits). If it was found then 1st call from Mobile Device 3 is on hold and 2nd call from Mobile Device 4 is active.\nclick Switch Call button with regex from HU display with found = click_on_device_regex(HU, "Switch") to switch between calls.\nwait 3 seconds for call switching to take effect.\ncheck if last 3 digits of mobile3 phone number can be found on HU display with found = find_word_on_device_via_regex(HU, last_3_digits). If it was found then 1st call from Mobile Device 3 is active and 2nd call from Mobile Device 4 is on hold.\ncheck if call switching functionality works properly by verifying both calls can be switched between with found == True. If is True, then multiparty call switching functionality works correctly and the test is Passed. If is False, call switching failed and the test is failed.\nplease make a screenshot on HU screen and save it on the path D:\\traget\\IDCevo\\IOP_configuration\\Test_results\\Screenshots.\nrun the following function on Mobile Device1: phone.end_call_command() in order to end call.\nrun the following function on Mobile Device1: phone.end_call_command() in order to end call.\nsave in Excel the status of the test (passed, failed or skipped) with the corresponding message.\nrun the following commands after test is done in order to return to home menu: HU commands: adb shell input keyevent 3 one time; adb shell rm /sdcard/*.png; Mobile device commands: rc = phone.run_home_command().\nstop screen recordings on HU after test is done with stop_screen_recording("HU") and keep them if test is failed or delete them if test is passed.\n'}, {'Test Case Description': '1 Initiate a call from Mobile Device 3 to Mobile Device 1.\n2 Accept call on HU.\n3 Initiate a call from Mobile Device 4 to Mobile Device 1.', 'Test Case Expected Result': '2 1st call from Mobile Device 3 is active. \n3 2nd call from Mobile Device 4 is incoming and Number is displayed.\nCall waiting tone is hearable and Accept/Reject is possible.', 'Test Case ID': 173021, 'Test Case Precondition': 'Mobile Device and HU are connected.\nSynchronisation is finished.\nIt is possible that the call waiting option is disabled for some SIM-cards. It is recommended to cheIDCEvo if this option is enabled. The status can be cheIDCEvoed by dialing the MMI code *#43#.', 'Test Name': 'Call_waiting', 'Test Script Description': '\n\ncheck USB Matrix status with status = USB_Matrix_Status().\nget serial numbers for them with HU, Mobile1 = get_serial_number().\nget Mobile device bluetooth name with adb shell settings get secure bluetooth_name.\ncreate recordings folder with create_recordings_folder() and start screen recording for HU with start_screen_recording(f"-s {HU}", test_name, "HU")(example for HU).\ncreate Mobile device object with phone = create_device(Mobile1,mobile_name).\nrun the following function on Mobile device: sim_state = phone.check_SIM_command(). If the command does not contain word LOADED Mobile device doesn\'t have SIM card on it and test is skipped.\nextract the mobile1 phone number with phone_number_mobile1 = phone.get_phone_number_command().\nclick Mobile device name button with regex from HU display with found = click_on_device_regex(HU, mobile_name).\nclick Contacts Button on from HU display with found = click_on_device(HU, "Contacts").\ncheck USB Matrix status with status = USB_Matrix_Status(). If USB Matrix is connected to port 1 then change it to port 2 and if is connected to any other port except port1 change the connection to port 1.\nget serial numbers for them with HU, Mobile3 = get_serial_number().\nget Mobile device bluetooth name with adb shell settings get secure bluetooth_name.\ncreate Mobile device3 object with phone3 = create_device(Mobile3,mobile_name3).\nrun the following function on Mobile device: sim_state = phone3.check_SIM_command(). If the command does not contain word LOADED Mobile device doesn\'t have SIM card on it and test is skipped.\nextract the mobile3 phone number with phone_number_mobile3 = phone3.get_phone_number_command().\nrun the following function on Mobile device3: rc = phone3.run_turn_screen_on_command() to turn Mobile3 screen on.\nrun the following function on Mobile device3: rc = phone3.run_unlock_screen_command() to unlock Mobile3 screen.\nrun the following function on Mobile device3: rc = phone3.dial_command(phone_number_mobile1) to initiate a call from Mobile Device 3 to Mobile Device 1. Wait 5 seconds for the call to be established.\nclick Accept button with regex from HU display with found = click_on_device_regex(HU, "Accept") to accept call on HU.\nswitch USB Matrix back to the port from the beginning with select_mobile_device(1, status).\ncheck USB Matrix status with status = USB_Matrix_Status(). If USB Matrix is connected to port 1 or 2 then change it to port 3 and if is connected to any other port except port1 or port 2 change the connection to port 2.\nget serial numbers for them with HU, Mobile4 = get_serial_number().\nget Mobile device bluetooth name with adb shell settings get secure bluetooth_name.\ncreate Mobile device4 object with phone4 = create_device(Mobile4,mobile_name4).\nrun the following function on Mobile device: sim_state = phone4.check_SIM_command(). If the command does not contain word LOADED Mobile device doesn\'t have SIM card on it and test is skipped.\nextract the mobile4 phone number with phone_number_mobile4 = phone4.get_phone_number_command().\nrun the following function on Mobile device4: rc = phone4.run_turn_screen_on_command() to turn Mobile4 screen on.\nrun the following function on Mobile device4: rc = phone4.run_unlock_screen_command() to unlock Mobile4 screen.\nrun the following function on Mobile device4: rc = phone4.dial_command(phone_number_mobile1) to initiate a call from Mobile Device 4 to Mobile Device 1. Wait 5 seconds for the second call to be established.\nswitch USB Matrix back to the port from the beginning with select_mobile_device(1, status).\ncheck if last 3 digits of mobile4 phone number can be found on HU display with found = find_word_on_device_via_regex(HU, last_3_digits). If it was found then 1st call from Mobile Device 3 is active and 2nd call from Mobile Device 4 is incoming with number displayed and call waiting tone is hearable with Accept/Reject possible and the test is Passed. If not then call waiting functionality is not working properly and the test is failed.\nplease make a screenshot on HU screen and save it on the path D:\\traget\\IDCevo\\IOP_configuration\\Test_results\\Screenshots.\nrun the following function on Mobile Device1: phone.end_call_command() in order to end call.\nsave in Excel the status of the test (passed, failed or skipped) with the corresponding message.\nrun the following function on Mobile Device1: phone.end_call_command() in order to end call.\nrun the following commands after test is done in order to return to home menu: HU commands: adb shell input keyevent 3 one time; adb shell rm /sdcard/*.png; Mobile device commands: rc = phone.run_home_command().\nstop screen recordings on HU after test is done with stop_screen_recording("HU") and keep them if test is failed or delete them if test is passed.\n\n'}, {'Test Case Description': '1 Initiate an incoming call from Mobile Device 3 to Mobile Device 1.\n2 Accept call on HU.\n3 End call on  HU.', 'Test Case Expected Result': '3 Call is terminated on HU and Mobile Device 1.', 'Test Case ID': 173020, 'Test Case Precondition': 'Mobile Device and HU are connected.\nSynchronisation is finished.', 'Test Name': 'End_call', 'Test Script Description': '\n\ncheck USB Matrix status with status = USB_Matrix_Status().\nget serial numbers for them with HU, Mobile1 = get_serial_number().\nget Mobile device bluetooth name with adb shell settings get secure bluetooth_name.\ncreate recordings folder with create_recordings_folder() and start screen recording for HU with start_screen_recording(f"-s {HU}", test_name, "HU")(example for HU).\ncreate Mobile device object with phone = create_device(Mobile1,mobile_name).\nrun the following function on Mobile device: sim_state = phone.check_SIM_command(). If the command does not contain word LOADED Mobile device doesn\'t have SIM card on it and test is skipped.\nextract the mobile1 phone number with phone_number_mobile1 = phone.get_phone_number_command().\nclick Mobile device name button with regex from HU display with found = click_on_device_regex(HU, mobile_name).\nclick Contacts Button on from HU display with found = click_on_device(HU, "Contacts").\ncheck USB Matrix status with status = USB_Matrix_Status(). If USB Matrix is connected to port 1 then change it to port 2 and if is connected to any other port except port1 change the connection to port 1.\nget serial numbers for them with HU, Mobile3 = get_serial_number().\nget Mobile device bluetooth name with adb shell settings get secure bluetooth_name.\ncreate Mobile device3 object with phone3 = create_device(Mobile3,mobile_name3).\nrun the following function on Mobile device: sim_state = phone3.check_SIM_command(). If the command does not contain word LOADED Mobile device doesn\'t have SIM card on it and test is skipped.\nextract the mobile3 phone number with phone_number_mobile3 = phone3.get_phone_number_command().\nrun the following function on Mobile device3: rc = phone3.run_turn_screen_on_command() to turn Mobile3 screen on.\nrun the following function on Mobile device3: rc = phone3.run_unlock_screen_command() to unlock Mobile3 screen.\nrun the following function on Mobile device3: rc = phone3.dial_command(phone_number_mobile1) to initiate an incoming call from Mobile Device 3 to Mobile Device 1. Wait 5 seconds for the incoming call to be established.\nclick Accept button with regex from HU display with found = click_on_device_regex(HU, "Accept") to accept call on HU.\nswitch USB Matrix back to the port from the beginning with select_mobile_device(1, status).\nwait 3 seconds for the call to become active.\nclick End Button on from HU display with regex with found = click_on_device_regex(HU, "End") or click Red Phone icon from HU display with x, y = find_icon_in_screenshot(f"{path}/screenshot.png", f"{path}/helpers/End_Call.png") to end call on HU.\nwait 3 seconds for the call to be terminated.\ncheck if "End" button was pressed successfully on HU display with found = "True". If it was pressed then call was terminated successfully on Mobile Device 1 and HU and the test is Passed. If not then call termination failed and the test is failed.\nplease make a screenshot on HU screen and save it on the path D:\\traget\\IDCevo\\IOP_configuration\\Test_results\\Screenshots.\nsave in Excel the status of the test (passed, failed or skipped) with the corresponding message.\nrun the following commands after test is done in order to return to home menu: HU commands: adb shell input keyevent 3 one time; adb shell rm /sdcard/*.png; Mobile device commands: rc = phone.run_home_command().\nstop screen recordings on HU after test is done with stop_screen_recording("HU") and keep them if test is failed or delete them if test is passed.\n\n'}, {'Test Case Description': '1 Power off HU.\nFor TestraIDCEvos and Testcases set mode Parken: "Parken_BN_IO".\n2 Wait until Head Unit sleeps.\n3 Initiate call from Mobile Device 3 to Mobile Device 1.\n4 With ongoing call power on HU.\nFor TestraIDCEvos and Testcases set mode Fahren: "Pruefen_Analyse_Diagnose".', 'Test Case Expected Result': '2 Head Unit sleeps.\n3 Call audio is audible on Mobile Device 1.\n4 After a couple of seconds call audio should be transfered to HU.\nAudio should be audible on both sides.', 'Test Case ID': 173019, 'Test Case Precondition': 'Mobile Device and HU are paired.\nSynchronisation is finished.', 'Test Name': 'Mobile_Device_transfer_call_to_HU_in_new_Lifecycle', 'Test Script Description': '\n\ncheck USB Matrix status with status = USB_Matrix_Status().\nget serial numbers for them with HU, Mobile1 = get_serial_number().\nget Mobile device bluetooth name with adb shell settings get secure bluetooth_name.\ncreate Mobile device object with phone = create_device(Mobile1,mobile_name).\nrun the following function on Mobile device: sim_state = phone.check_SIM_command(). If the command does not contain word LOADED Mobile device doesn\'t have SIM card on it and test is skipped.\nextract the mobile1 phone number with phone_number_mobile1 = phone.get_phone_number_command().\ncheck USB Matrix status with status = USB_Matrix_Status(). If USB Matrix is connected to port 1 then change it to port 2 and if is connected to any other port except port1 change the connection to port 1.\nget serial numbers for them with HU, Mobile3 = get_serial_number().\nget Mobile device bluetooth name with adb shell settings get secure bluetooth_name.\ncreate Mobile device3 object with phone3 = create_device(Mobile3,mobile_name3).\nrun the following function on Mobile device: sim_state = phone3.check_SIM_command(). If the command does not contain word LOADED Mobile device doesn\'t have SIM card on it and test is skipped.\nextract the mobile3 phone number with phone_number_mobile3 = phone3.get_phone_number_command().\nrun the following adb commands on HU: adb root; adb pull /data/misc/bluetooth/logs/btsnoop_hci.log btsnoop_hci_before_poweroff_transfer.log; adb pull /data/misc/bluetooth/logs/btsnoop_hci.log.last btsnoop_hci_before_poweroff_transfer.log.last; move btsnoop* D:/traget/IDCevo/IOP_configuration/Test_results in order to extract BTsnoop logs from HU before power off.\nrun the following function: power_off_HU() on HU to power off HU. Wait 10 seconds for HU to completely power off.\nswitch USB Matrix back to the port from the beginning with select_mobile_device_1(1, status).\nrun the following function on Mobile device3: rc = phone3.run_turn_screen_on_command() to turn Mobile3 screen on.\nrun the following function on Mobile device3: rc = phone3.run_unlock_screen_command() to unlock Mobile3 screen.\nrun the following function on Mobile device3: rc = phone3.dial_command(phone_number_mobile1) to initiate call from Mobile Device 3 to Mobile Device 1. Wait 5 seconds for the incoming call to be established.\ncheck USB Matrix status with status = USB_Matrix_Status(). If USB Matrix is connected to port 1 then change it to port 2 and if is connected to any other port except port1 change the connection to port 1.\nrun the following function on Mobile device3: rc = phone3.answer_call_command() to answer the call.\nswitch USB Matrix back to the port from the beginning with select_mobile_device_1(1, status).\nrun the following function to power on HU: power_on_HU() with ongoing call. Wait 60 seconds for HU to boot up and establish Bluetooth connection.\nrun the following command in Windows cmd to resume DLT logs after reboot: ssh -i id_ed25519_idcevo -o StrictHostKeyChecking=no -o ConnectTimeout=10 root@160.48.249.99 "nohup dlt-receive -a localhost -o /var/data/{mobile_name_without_space}.dlt >/dev/null 2>&1 &".\nclick Retry icon button from PC display with click_on_Retry(). Wait 30 seconds for HU to initialize properly.\nget serial numbers for them with HU, Mobile1 = get_serial_number().\nclick X icon from HU display 2 times with x, y = find_icon_in_screenshot(f"{path}/screenshot.png", f"{path}/helpers/X.png") or x, y = find_icon_in_screenshot(f"{path}/screenshot.png", f"{path}/helpers/X_2.png").\nclick X_black icon from HU display 4 times with x, y = find_icon_in_screenshot(f"{path}/screenshot.png", f"{path}/helpers/X_black.png").\nrun the following adb commands on HU: adb shell device_config put bluetooth INIT_default_log_level_str LOG_VERBOSE to restart BTsnoop logging after power on.\nrun the following 2 adb commands on HU: adb shell am start -a android.settings.LOCALE_SETTINGS; adb shell input swipe 1200 500 2000 200 to Navigate on Language Menu.\nclick English Button from HU display with regex with found = click_on_device_regex(HU, "English"). If found == False run the following adb commands on HU: adb shell input tap 200 700; adb shell input swipe 1200 500 2000 200 then click English button again with found = click_on_device_regex(HU, "English").\nrun the following adb command on HU: adb shell input tap 3000 650.\ncheck if last 3 digits of mobile3 phone number can be found on HU display with found = find_word_on_device_via_regex(HU, last_3_digits). If it was found then Head Unit sleeps, call audio is audible on Mobile Device 1, and after a couple of seconds call audio should be transferred to HU with audio audible on both sides and the test is Passed. If not then call transfer to HU in new lifecycle failed and the test is failed.\nplease make a screenshot on HU screen and save it on the path D:\\traget\\IDCevo\\IOP_configuration\\Test_results\\Screenshots.\nrun the following function on Mobile Device1: phone.end_call_command() in order to end call.\nsave in Excel the status of the test (passed, failed or skipped) with the corresponding message.\nrun the following commands after test is done in order to return to home menu: HU commands: adb shell input keyevent 3 one time; adb shell rm /sdcard/*.png; Mobile device commands: rc = phone.run_home_command().\n\n'}, {'Test Case Description': '1 Initiate an incoming call from Mobile Device 3 to Mobile Device 1.\n2 Accept call on HU.\n3 On HU Menue in active call transfer audio to Mobile device 1.', 'Test Case Expected Result': '3 Audio is only audible on Mobile Device 1.', 'Test Case ID': 173018, 'Test Case Precondition': 'Mobile Device and HU are connected.\nSynchronisation is finished.', 'Test Name': 'HU_transfer_audio_to_Mobile_Device', 'Test Script Description': '\n\n\ncheck USB Matrix status with status = USB_Matrix_Status().\nget serial numbers for them with HU, Mobile1 = get_serial_number().\nget Mobile device bluetooth name with adb shell settings get secure bluetooth_name.\ncreate recordings folder with create_recordings_folder() and start screen recording for HU with start_screen_recording(f"-s {HU}", test_name, "HU")(example for HU).\ncreate Mobile device object with phone = create_device(Mobile1,mobile_name).\nrun the following function on Mobile device: sim_state = phone.check_SIM_command(). If the command does not contain word LOADED Mobile device doesn\'t have SIM card on it and test is skipped.\nextract the mobile1 phone number with phone_number_mobile1 = phone.get_phone_number_command().\nclick Mobile device name button with regex from HU display with found = click_on_device_regex(HU, mobile_name).\nclick Contacts Button on from HU display with found = click_on_device(HU, "Contacts").\ncheck USB Matrix status with status = USB_Matrix_Status(). If USB Matrix is connected to port 1 then change it to port 2 and if is connected to any other port except port1 change the connection to port 1.\nget serial numbers for them with HU, Mobile3 = get_serial_number().\nget Mobile device bluetooth name with adb shell settings get secure bluetooth_name.\ncreate Mobile device3 object with phone3 = create_device(Mobile3,mobile_name3).\nrun the following function on Mobile device: sim_state = phone3.check_SIM_command(). If the command does not contain word LOADED Mobile device doesn\'t have SIM card on it and test is skipped.\nextract the mobile3 phone number with phone_number_mobile3 = phone3.get_phone_number_command().\nrun the following function on Mobile device3: rc = phone3.run_turn_screen_on_command() to turn Mobile3 screen on.\nrun the following function on Mobile device3: rc = phone3.run_unlock_screen_command() to unlock Mobile3 screen.\nrun the following function on Mobile device3: rc = phone3.dial_command(phone_number_mobile1) to initiate an incoming call from Mobile Device 3 to Mobile Device 1. Wait 5 seconds for the incoming call to be established.\nclick Accept button with regex from HU display with found = click_on_device_regex(HU, "Accept") to accept the call on HU.\nswitch USB Matrix back to the port from the beginning with select_mobile_device(1, status).\nextract bluetooth_device_name for HU in a variable using the following adb command: adb shell dumpsys bluetooth_manager | findstr -i "Name:".\nrun the following function on Mobile device1: found = phone.transfer_audio_to_HU(bluetooth_device_name) to change speaker and transfer audio to HU speaker. Wait 3 seconds for audio transfer to take effect.\nclick Transfer button with regex from HU display with found = click_on_device_regex(HU, "Transfer") to transfer the audio on Mobile device1.\ncheck if audio transfer is successful on Mobile Device 1 with found == True. If is True, then audio transfer functionality works correctly and the test is Passed. If is False, audio transfer failed and the test is failed.\nplease make a screenshot on HU screen and save it on the path D:\\traget\\IDCevo\\IOP_configuration\\Test_results\\Screenshots.\nrun the following function on Mobile Device1: phone.end_call_command() in order to end call.\nsave in Excel the status of the test (passed, failed or skipped) with the corresponding message.\nrun the following commands after test is done in order to return to home menu: HU commands: adb shell input keyevent 3 one time; adb shell rm /sdcard/*.png; Mobile device commands: rc = phone.run_home_command().\nstop screen recordings on HU after test is done with stop_screen_recording("HU") and keep them if test is failed or delete them if test is passed.\n\n\n'}, {'Test Case Description': '1 Initiate an incoming call from Mobile Device 3 to Mobile Device 1.\n2 Accept call on HU..\n3 On Mobile Device 1 (connected device)  navigate to change speaker and transfer audio to Mobile Device speaker.\n4 On Mobile Device 1 (connected device)  navigate to change speaker and transfer audio to HU.', 'Test Case Expected Result': '3 Audio is only audible on Mobile Device 1.\n4 Audio is only audible on HU.', 'Test Case ID': 173017, 'Test Case Precondition': 'Mobile Device and HU are connected.\nSynchronisation is finished.', 'Test Name': 'Mobile_Device_transfer_audio_to_HU', 'Test Script Description': '\n\ncheck USB Matrix status with status = USB_Matrix_Status().\nget serial numbers for them with HU, Mobile1 = get_serial_number().\nget Mobile device bluetooth name with adb shell settings get secure bluetooth_name.\ncreate recordings folder with create_recordings_folder() and start screen recording for HU with start_screen_recording(f"-s {HU}", test_name, "HU")(example for HU).\ncreate Mobile device object with phone = create_device(Mobile1,mobile_name).\nrun the following function on Mobile device: sim_state = phone.check_SIM_command(). If the command does not contain word LOADED Mobile 