ing call to be established.\nclick Accept button with regex from HU display with found = click_on_device_regex(HU, "Accept") to accept the call on HU.\nrun the following function on Mobile device3: rc = phone3.mute_unmute_microphone_command() to mute microphone on Mobile Device 3 during the active call. wait 3 seconds for microphone mute to take effect.\nswitch USB Matrix back to the port from the beginning with select_mobile_device(1, status).\ncheck if microphone is muted by verifying no audio is transmitted from Mobile Device 3 to HU with found == True. If is True, then microphone mute functionality works correctly and the test is Passed. If is Flase, audio is still being transmitted then microphone mute failed and the test is failed.\nplease make a screenshot on HU screen and save it on the path D:\\traget\\IDCevo\\IOP_configuration\\Test_results\\Screenshots.\nrun the following function on Mobile Device1: phone.end_call_command() in order to end call.\nsave in Excel the status of the test (passed, failed or skipped) with the corresponding message.\nrun the following commands after test is done in order to return to home menu: HU commands: adb shell input keyevent 3 one time; adb shell rm /sdcard/*.png; Mobile device commands: rc = phone.run_home_command().\nstop screen recordings on HU after test is done with stop_screen_recording("HU") and keep them if test is failed or delete them if test is passed.\n\n\n'}, {'Test Case Description': '1 Initiate an outgoing call from Mobile Device 1 to Mobile Device 3.\n2 Accept call on Mobile Device 3.\n3 During an active call navigate on HU to Keypad dialing and dial several numbers.', 'Test Case Expected Result': '3 CheIDCEvo if DTMF-Tone is audible on Mobile Device 3.', 'Test Case ID': 173014, 'Test Case Precondition': 'Mobile Device and HU are connected.\nSynchronisation is finished.', 'Test Name': 'DTMF_Tone', 'Test Script Description': '\ncheck USB Matrix status with status = USB_Matrix_Status().\nget serial numbers for them with HU, Mobile1 = get_serial_number().\nget Mobile device bluetooth name with adb shell settings get secure bluetooth_name.\ncreate recordings folder with create_recordings_folder() and start screen recording for HU with start_screen_recording(f"-s {HU}", test_name, "HU")(example for HU).\ncreate Mobile device object with phone = create_device(Mobile1,mobile_name).\nrun the following function on Mobile device: sim_state = phone.check_SIM_command(). If the command does not contain word LOADED Mobile device doesn\'t have SIM card on it and test is skipped.\nextract the mobile1 phone number with phone_number_mobile1 = phone.get_phone_number_command().\ncheck USB Matrix status with status = USB_Matrix_Status(). If USB Matrix is connected to port 1 then change it to port 2 and if is connected to any other port except port1 change the connection to port 1.\nget serial numbers for them with HU, Mobile3 = get_serial_number().\nget Mobile device bluetooth name with adb shell settings get secure bluetooth_name.\ncreate Mobile device3 object with phone3 = create_device(Mobile3,mobile_name).\nrun the following function on Mobile device: sim_state = phone3.check_SIM_command(). If the command does not contain word LOADED Mobile device doesn\'t have SIM card on it and test is skipped.\nextract the mobile3 phone number with phone_number_mobile3 = phone3.get_phone_number_command().\nswitch USB Matrix back to the port from the beginning with select_mobile_device(1, status).\nclick Mobile device name button with regex from HU display with found = click_on_device_regex(HU, mobile_name).\nclick Contacts Button on from HU display with found = click_on_device(HU, "Contacts").\nrun the following function on Mobile device: rc = phone.run_turn_screen_on_command() to turn Mobile screen on.\nrun the following function on Mobile device: rc = phone.run_unlock_screen_command() to unlock Mobile screen.\nrun the following function on Mobile device: rc = phone.dial_command(phone_number_mobile3) to initiate a call to Mobile3. Wait 5 seconds for the call to start setting up.\ncheck USB Matrix status with status = USB_Matrix_Status(). If USB Matrix is connected to port 1 then change it to port 2 and if is connected to any other port except port1 change the connection to port 1.\nrun the following function on Mobile device3: rc = phone3.answer_call_command() to accept the call from Mobile1.\nclick Left Arrow icon from HU display with x, y = find_icon_in_screenshot(f"{path}/screenshot.png", f"{path}/helpers/Left_Arrow.png") or x, y = find_icon_in_screenshot(f"{path}/screenshot.png", f"{path}/helpers/Left_Arrow_2.png").\nswitch USB Matrix back to the port from the beginning with select_mobile_device(1, status).\nwait 3 seconds for the call to become active.\nclick Keypad Button on from HU display with found = click_on_device(HU, "Dial") to navigate to keypad dialing.\nclick number buttons on HU keypad to dial several numbers with found = click_on_device(HU, "1"); found = click_on_device(HU, "2"); found = click_on_device(HU, "3").\ncheck if DTMF tone is audible on Mobile device3 by verifying if dialed numbers are received properly with dtmf_success = find_word_on_device_via_regex(HU,"123"). If they are found on HU display, DTMF tones are transmitted correctly then the test is Passed. If not then DTMF tone transmission failed and the test is failed.\nplease make a screenshot on HU screen and save it on the path D:\\traget\\IDCevo\\IOP_configuration\\Test_results\\Screenshots.\nrun the following function on Mobile Device: phone.end_call_command() in order to end call.\nclick Contacts Button on from HU display with found = click_on_device(HU, "Contacts").\nsave in Excel the status of the test (passed, failed or skipped) with the corresponding message.\nrun the following commands after test is done in order to return to home menu: HU commands: adb shell input keyevent 3 one time; adb shell rm /sdcard/*.png; Mobile device commands: rc = phone.run_home_command().\nstop screen recordings on HU after test is done with stop_screen_recording("HU") and keep them if test is failed or delete them if test is passed.\n'}, {'Test Case Description': '1 Initiate an incoming call from Mobile Device 3 to Mobile Device 1.\n2 Power off HU during active call.\nFor TestraIDCEvos and Testcases set mode Parken: "Parken_BN_IO".', 'Test Case Expected Result': '2 Bluetooth connection is released. Call is transfered to Mobile Device 1. Audio and voice are audible on Mobile Device 1 and Mobile Device 3.', 'Test Case ID': 173013, 'Test Case Precondition': 'Mobile Device and HU are connected.\nSynchronisation is finished.', 'Test Name': 'Power_off_HU_during_active_call', 'Test Script Description': '\n\ncheck USB Matrix status with status = USB_Matrix_Status().\nget serial numbers for them with HU, Mobile1 = get_serial_number().\nget Mobile device bluetooth name with adb shell settings get secure bluetooth_name.\ncreate Mobile device object with phone = create_device(Mobile1,mobile_name).\nrun the following function on Mobile device: sim_state = phone.check_SIM_command(). If the command does not contain word LOADED Mobile device doesn\'t have SIM card on it and test is skipped.\nextract the mobile1 phone number with phone_number_mobile1 = phone.get_phone_number_command().\nclick Mobile device name button with regex from HU display with found = click_on_device_regex(HU, mobile_name).\nclick Contacts Button on from HU display with found = click_on_device(HU, "Contacts").\ncheck USB Matrix status with status = USB_Matrix_Status(). If USB Matrix is connected to port 1 then change it to port 2 and if is connected to any other port except port1 change the connection to port 1.\nget serial numbers for them with HU, Mobile3 = get_serial_number().\nget Mobile device bluetooth name with adb shell settings get secure bluetooth_name.\ncreate Mobile device3 object with phone3 = create_device(Mobile3,mobile_name).\nrun the following function on Mobile device: sim_state = phone3.check_SIM_command(). If the command does not contain word LOADED Mobile device doesn\'t have SIM card on it and test is skipped.\nextract the mobile3 phone number with phone_number_mobile3 = phone3.get_phone_number_command().\nrun the following function on Mobile device3: rc = phone3.run_turn_screen_on_command() to turn Mobile3 screen on.\nrun the following function on Mobile device3: rc = phone3.run_unlock_screen_command() to unlock Mobile3 screen.\nrun the following function on Mobile device3: rc = phone3.dial_command(phone_number_mobile1) to initiate an incoming call from Mobile Device 3 to Mobile Device 1. Wait 5 seconds for the incoming call to be established.\nclick Accept button with regex from HU display with found = click_on_device_regex(HU, "Accept") to accept the call on HU. Wait 3 seconds for the call to become active.\nswitch USB Matrix back to the port from the beginning with select_mobile_device(1, status).\nrun the following adb commands on HU: adb root; adb pull /data/misc/bluetooth/logs/btsnoop_hci.log btsnoop_hci_before_poweroff_active.log; adb pull /data/misc/bluetooth/logs/btsnoop_hci.log.last btsnoop_hci_before_poweroff_active.log.last; move btsnoop* D:/traget/IDCevo/IOP_configuration/Test_results in order to extract BTsnoop logs from HU before power off.\nrun the following function: power_off_HU() on HU to power off HU during active call.Wait 10 seconds for HU to completely power off.\nrun the following function on Mobile device: rc = phone.run_turn_screen_on_command() to turn Mobile screen on.\nrun the following function on Mobile device: rc = phone.run_unlock_screen_command() to unlock Mobile screen.\nrun the following function on Mobile device: phone.run_settings_menu_command() go to Mobile Settings menu.\nrun the following function on Mobile device: rc = phone.run_bluetooth_menu_command() go to Mobile Bluetooth menu.\ncheck if bluetooth connection was released after HU power off with found = phone.check_bluetooth_connection(). If found contains the following text: ConnectionState: STATE_DISCONNECTED then Bluetooth connection was released and call is transferred to Mobile Device 1 and the test is Passed. If not then call was terminated or connection remained active and the test is Failed.\nplease make a screenshot on Mobile device screen and save it on the path D:\\traget\\IDCevo\\IOP_configuration\\Test_results\\Screenshots.\nrun the following function to power on HU: power_on_HU() during incoming call. Wait 60 seconds for HU to boot up and establish Bluetooth connection.\nrun the following command in Windows cmd to resume DLT logs after reboot: ssh -i id_ed25519_idcevo -o StrictHostKeyChecking=no -o ConnectTimeout=10 root@160.48.249.99 "nohup dlt-receive -a localhost -o /var/data/{mobile_name_without_space}.dlt >/dev/null 2>&1 &".\nclick Retry icon button from PC display with click_on_Retry(). Wait 30 seconds for HU to initialize properly.\nget serial numbers for them with HU, Mobile1 = get_serial_number().\nclick X icon from HU display 2 times with x, y = find_icon_in_screenshot(f"{path}/screenshot.png", f"{path}/helpers/X.png") or x, y = find_icon_in_screenshot(f"{path}/screenshot.png", f"{path}/helpers/X_2.png").\nclick X_black icon from HU display 4 times with x, y = find_icon_in_screenshot(f"{path}/screenshot.png", f"{path}/helpers/X_black.png").\nrun the following adb commands on HU: adb shell device_config put bluetooth INIT_default_log_level_str LOG_VERBOSE to restart BTsnoop logging after power on.\nrun the following 2 adb commands on HU: adb shell am start -a android.settings.LOCALE_SETTINGS; adb shell input swipe 1200 500 2000 200 to Navigate on Language Menu.\nclick English Button from HU display with regex with found = click_on_device_regex(HU, "English"). If found == False run the following adb commands on HU: adb shell input tap 200 700; adb shell input swipe 1200 500 2000 200 then click English button again with found = click_on_device_regex(HU, "English").\nrun the follo