le device: rc = phone.run_bluetooth_menu_command() go to Mobile Bluetooth menu.\ncheck if bluetooth connection was released after HU power off with found = phone.check_bluetooth_connection(). If found contains the following text: ConnectionState: STATE_DISCONNECTED then Bluetooth connection was released and audio is still audible on Mobile Device and the test is Passed. If not then call was terminated and some implementations might hang up and the test is Failed.\nplease make a screenshot on Mobile device screen and save it on the path D:\\traget\\IDCevo\\IOP_configuration\\Test_results\\Screenshots.\nrun the following function on Mobile Device1: phone.end_call_command() in order to end call.\nsave in Excel the status of the test (passed, failed or skipped) with the corresponding message.\nrun the following commands after test is done in order to return to home menu: Mobile device commands: rc = phone.run_home_command().\n\n\n"}, {'Test Case Description': '1 Initiate an outgoing call from Mobile Device 1 to Mobile Device 3.\n2 Accept call on Mobile Device 3.\n3 Terminate call on HU.', 'Test Case Expected Result': '3 Call is terminated on Mobile Device and HU.', 'Test Case ID': 173005, 'Test Case Precondition': 'Mobile Device and HU are connected.\nSynchronisation is finished.', 'Test Name': 'Terminate_active_call', 'Test Script Description': '\ncheck USB Matrix status with status = USB_Matrix_Status().\nget serial numbers for them with HU, Mobile1 = get_serial_number().\nget Mobile device bluetooth name with adb shell settings get secure bluetooth_name.\ncreate recordings folder with create_recordings_folder() and start screen recording for HU with start_screen_recording(f"-s {HU}", test_name, "HU")(example for HU).\ncreate Mobile device object with phone = create_device(Mobile1,mobile_name).\nrun the following function on Mobile device: sim_state = phone.check_SIM_command(). If the command does not contain word LOADED Mobile device doesn\'t have SIM card on it and 