following adb command on HU: adb shell input keyevent 3.\nclick Mobile device name button with regex from HU display with found = click_on_device_regex(HU, mobile_name).\nrun the following adb command on HU display: adb shell input swipe 1700 700 200 2500.\nsave in Excel the status of the test (passed, failed or skipped) with the corresponding message.\nrun the following commands after test is done in order to return to home menu: HU commands: adb shell input keyevent 3 one time; adb shell rm /sdcard/*.png; Mobile device commands: rc = phone.run_home_command().\nstop screen recordings on HU after test is done with stop_screen_recording("HU") and keep them if test is failed or delete them if test is passed.\n\n'}, {'Test Case Description': '1 Put Mobile Device in shielding bag or shielding chamber.\n2 Get Mobile Device out of shielding bag or shielding chamber. Wait a few seconds.', 'Test Case Expected Result': '1 Bluetooth connection is released.\n2 Bluetooth connection is re-established. Phone icon on display of HU is visible.', 'Test Case ID': 173001, 'Test Case Precondition': 'Mobile Device and HU are paired.\nMobile Device is connected as hands-free device (network indicator can be seen in the display of the HU).\nTo simulate the linkloss a shielding bag or shielding chamber is recommended.', 'Test Name': 'HFP_conn', 'Test Script Description': '\ncheck USB Matrix status with status = USB_Matrix_Status().\nget serial numbers for them with HU, Mobile1 = get_serial_number().\ncreate recordings folder with create_recordings_folder() and start screen recording for HU with start_screen_recording(f"-s {HU}", test_name, "HU").\nget Mobile device bluetooth name with adb shell settings get secure bluetooth_name.\ncreate Mobile device object with phone = create_device(Mobile1,mobile_name).\nclick Bluetooth icon from HU display with x,y = find_icon_in_screenshot(f"{path}/screenshot.png",f"{path}/helpers/Bluetooth.png") or x,y = find_icon_in_screenshot(f"{path}/screenshot.png",f"{path}/helpers/Bluetooth_2.png").\nclick Manage Devices Button from HU display with found = click_on_device(HU,"Manage devices").\nclick Smartphones Button on from HU display with found = click_on_device(HU,"Smartphones").\nrun the following function on Mobile device: phone.enable_airplane_mode_command() to simulate putting Mobile Device in shielding bag or shielding chamber. Wait 5 seconds with airplane mode enabled.\nrun the following function on Mobile device: phone.disable_airplane_mode_command() to disable airplane mode.\nrun the following function on Mobile device: phone.run_linkloss_command() to simulate getting Mobile Device out of shielding bag or shielding chamber. Wait 15 seconds for bluetooth connection to be re-established.\ncheck if "Connected" word can be found on HU display with found = find_word_on_device(HU,"Connected"). If it was found then Bluetooth connection is re-established and Phone icon on display of HU is visible and the test is Passed. If not then Bluetooth connection was not re-established after removing from shielding and the test is failed.\nplease make a screenshot on HU screen and save it on the path D:\\traget\\IDCevo\\IOP_configuration\\Test_results\\Screenshots.\nsave in Excel the status of the test (passed or failed) with the corresponding message.\nrun the following commmands after test is done in order to return to home menu: HU commands: adb shell input keyevent 3 one time; adb shell rm /sdcard/*.png.\nstop screen recordings on HU after test is done with stop_screen_recording("HU") and keep them if test is failed or delete them if test is passed.\n'}, {'Test Case Description': '1 CheIDCEvo if timestamps on Mobile Device and HU for call history are the same.', 'Test Case Expected Result': '1 Timestamps are correct.', 'Test Case ID': 172999, 'Test Case Precondition': 'Mobile Device and HU are connected.\nSynchronisation is finished.\nSome calls are listed in call list.', 'Test Name': 'Time_stamps', 'Test Script Description': '\n\ncheck USB Matrix status with status = USB_Matrix_Status().\nget serial numbers for them with HU, Mobile1 = get_serial_number().\ncreate recordings folder with create_recordings_folder() and start screen recording for HU with start_screen_recording(f"-s {HU}", test_name, "HU")(example for HU).\nget Mobile device bluetooth name with adb shell settings get secure bluetooth_name.\ncreate Mobile device object with phone = create_device(Mobile1,mobile_name).\nclick Mobile device name button with regex from HU display with found = click_on_device_regex(HU, mobile_name).\nclick Calls Button on from HU display with found = click_on_device(HU, "Calls").\nrun the following function on mobile device: result = phone.get_call_history_with_timestamps().\ncheck if mobile device timestamp can be found on HU display with found = click_on_device_via_regex(HU, mobile_timestamps). If it was found then call history timestamps are synchronized correctly between Mobile device and HU and the test is Passed. If it was not found run the following adb command: adb shell input swipe 1700 700 2000 200 to scroll down on contacts list from HU display. Try it for 10 times if the extracted contact was not found the test is failed. \nplease make a screenshot on HU screen and save it on the path D:\\traget\\IDCevo\\IOP_configuration\\Test_results\\Screenshots.\nrun the following adb command on HU: adb shell input keyevent 3.\nclick Mobile device name button with regex from HU display with found = click_on_device_regex(HU, mobile_name).\nrun the following adb command on HU display: adb shell input swipe 1700 700 200 2500.\nsave in Excel the status of the test (passed or failed) with the corresponding message.\nrun the following commmands after test is done in order to return to home menu: HU commands: adb shell input keyevent 3 one time; adb shell rm /sdcard/*.png.\nstop screen recordings on HU after test is done with stop_screen_recording("HU") and keep them if test is failed or delete them if 