st is failed or delete them if test is passed.'}, {'Test Case Description': '1 On HUgo to Communication --> Contacts\n2 Go to a random address. CheIDCEvo all adress elements.\n3 Start navigation to selected address.\n\n', 'Test Case Expected Result': '2 Address elements (Street, street number, postal code, company) are displayed correctly.\n3 Navigation to selected address is started.\n', 'Test Case ID': 172988, 'Test Case Precondition': 'Mobile Device and HU are connected.\nPhonebook download is finished.\n', 'Test Name': 'Postal_address', 'Test Script Description': 'check USB Matrix status with status = USB_Matrix_Status().\nget serial numbers for them with HU, Mobile1 = get_serial_number().\ncreate recordings folder with create_recordings_folder() and start screen recording for HU with start_screen_recording(f"-s {HU}", test_name, "HU")(example for HU).\nget Mobile device bluetooth name with adb shell settings get secure bluetooth_name.\ncreate Mobile device object with phone = create_device(Mobile1,mobile_name).\nclick Contacts Button on from HU display with found = click_on_device(HU, "Contacts").\nrun the following function on mobile device: stdout = phone.get_contacts_name_with_postal_address_command().\nextract the first contact for with postal address in the name. Check if the contact last name is available with stdout = phone.get_contacts_data3_command() and if it is save it in a variable. If not save the whole name in a variable with stdout = phone.get_contacts_data2_command().\nclick on the extracted name Button on from HU display with found = click_on_device_with_verification(HU, click_target). If it was not found run the following adb command: adb shell input swipe 1700 700 2000 200 to scroll down on contacts list from HU display. Try it for 10 times if the extracted contact was not found the test is failed.\ncheck if Private word can be found on HU display with regex with found = find_word_on_device_via_regex(HU, "Private"). If it was found then Mobile device Contact with postal adress is displayed successfully on HU and the test is Passed. If not then Mobile device Contact with postal adress is not displayed and the test is failed.\nplease make a screenshot on HU screen and save it on the path D:\\traget\\IDCevo\\IOP_configuration\\Test_results\\Screenshots.\nrun the following adb command on HU: adb shell input keyevent 3.\nclick Mobile device name button with regex from HU display with found = click_on_device_regex(HU, mobile_name).\nrun the following adb command on HU display: adb shell input swipe 1700 700 200 2500.\nsave in Excel the status of the test (passed or failed) with the corresponding message.\nrun the following commmands after test is done in order to return to home menu: HU commands: adb shell input keyevent 3 one time; adb shell rm /sdcard/*.png.\nstop screen recordings on HU and Mobile after test is done with stop_screen_recording("HU") and keep them if test is failed or delete them if test is passed.'}, {'Test Case Description': '1 Go to Communications --> Contacts\n2 Go to a contact that has blanks in its contact details.\n', 'Test Case Expected Result': '2 Blanks are displayed correctly.', 'Test Case ID': 172987, 'Test Case Precondition': 'Mobile Device and HU are connected.\nPhonebook download is finished.\nA contact with blanks (some spaces between charakters) in contact details is stored in Phonebook.', 'Test Name': 'Blanks_in_contact_details', 'Test Script Description': 'check USB Matrix status with status = USB_Matrix_Status().\nget serial numbers for them with HU, Mobile1 = get_serial_number().\ncreate recordings folder with create_recordings_folder() and start screen recording for HU with start_screen_recording(f"-s {HU}", test_name, "HU")(example for HU).\nget Mobile device bluetooth name with adb shell settings get secure bluetooth_name.\ncreate Mobile device object with phone = create_device(Mobile1,mobile_name).\nclick Mobile device name button with regex from HU display with found = click_on_device_regex(HU, mobile_name).\nclick Contacts Button on from HU display with found = click_on_device(HU, "Contacts").\nrun the following function on mobile device: stdout = phone.get_contacts_name_command(). Extract the display_name for all contacts displayed in a list.\nrun the following function on mobile device: stdout = phone.get_contacts_name_with_postal_address_command(). Extract the display_name for all contacts with postal address displayed in a list.\nextract the first contact for with a blank postal address in the name.Check if the contact last name is available with stdout = phone.get_contacts_data3_command() and if it is save it in a variable. If not save the whole name in a variable with stdout = phone.get_contacts_data2_command().\nclick on the extracted name Button on from HU display with found = click_on_device_with_verification(HU, click_target). If it was not found run the following adb command: adb shell input swipe 1700 700 2000 200 to scroll down on contacts list from HU display. Try it for 10 times if the extracted contact was not found the test is failed.\ncheck if contact found word can be found on HU display with found = find_word_on_device_via_regex(HU, click_target). If it was found then Mobile device Contact with blank details is displayed successfully on HU and the test is Passed. If not then Mobile device Contact with blank details is not displayed and the test is failed.\nplease make a screenshot on HU screen and save it on the path D:\\traget\\IDCevo\\IOP_configuration\\Test_results\\Screenshots.\nrun the following adb command on HU: adb shell input keyevent 3.\nclick Mobile device name button with regex from HU display with found = click_on_device_regex(HU, mobile_name).\nrun the following adb command on HU display: adb shell input swipe 1700 700 200 2500.\nsave in Excel the status of the test (passed or failed) with the corresponding message.\nrun the following commmands after test is done in order to return to home menu: HU commands: adb shell input keyevent 3 one time; adb shell rm /sdcard/*.png.\nstop screen recordings on HU and Mobile after test is done with stop_screen_recording("HU") and keep them if test is failed or delete them if test is passed.'}, {'Test Case Description': '1 On IDCEvo go to Communication --> Contacts\n2 Go to any contact with special characters in name or other fields.\n\n', 'Test Case Expected Result': '2 All special characters displayed correctly.', 'Test Case ID': 172986, 'Test Case Precondition': 'Mobile Device and HU are connected.\nPhonebook download is finished.\nPhonebook has contacts with special characters (e.g.: &, $,%, §, ä, ü, ö)', 'Test Name': 'Special_characters', 'Test Script Description': 'check USB Matrix status with status = USB_Matrix_Status().\nget serial numbers for them with HU, Mobile1 = get_serial_number().\ncreate recordings folder with create_recordings_folder() and start screen recording for HU with start_screen_recording(f"-s {HU}", test_name, "HU")(example for HU).\nget Mobile device bluetooth name with adb shell settings get secure bluetooth_name.\ncreate Mobile device object with phone = create_device(Mobile1,mobile_name).\nclick Mobile device name button with regex from HU display with found = click_on_device_regex(HU, mobile_name).\nclick Contacts Button on from HU display with found = click_on_device(HU, "Contacts").\nrun the following function on mobile device: stdout = phone.get_contacts_name_command().\nextract the first contact for which contains special charaters in the name. Check if the contact last name is available with stdout = phone.get_contacts_data3_command() and if it is save it in a variable. If not save the whole name in a variable with stdout = phone.get_contacts_data2_command().\nclick on the extracted name Button on from HU display with found = click_on_device_with_verification(HU, click_target). If it was not found run the following adb command: adb shell input swipe 1700 700 2000 200 to scroll down on contacts list from HU display. Try it for 10 times if the extracted contact was not found the test is failed.\ncheck if special characters from the name word can be found on HU display with regex with special_chars_in_name = special_chars_pattern.findall(click_target). If it was found then Mobile device Contact with special characters is displayed successfully on HU and the test is Passed. If not then Mobile device Contact with special characters is not displayed and the test is failed.\nplease make a screenshot on HU screen and save it on the path D:\\traget\\IDCevo\\IOP_configuration\\Test_results\\Screenshots.\nrun the following adb command on HU: adb shell input keyevent 3.\nclick Mobile device name button with regex from HU display with found = click_on_device_regex(HU, mobile_name).\nrun the following adb command on HU display: adb shell input swipe 1700 700 200 2500.\nsave in Excel the status of the test (passed or failed) with the corresponding message.\nrun the following commmands after test is done in order to return to home menu: HU commands: adb shell input keyevent 3 one time; adb shell rm /sdcard/*.png.\nstop screen recordings on HU and Mobile after test is done with stop_screen_recording("HU") and keep them if test is failed or delete them if test is passed.'}, {'Test Case Description': '1 Go to Communication --> Contacts\n2 CheIDCEvo if pictures are displayed correctly.\n', 'Test Case Expected Result': '2 Contact picture of contacts are displayed correctly.', 'Test Case ID': 172985, 'Test Case Precondition': 'Mobile Device and HU are connected.\nPhonebook download is finished.\nSync animation can`t be seen anymore.\nContactbook has contacs with picture.', 'Test Name': 'Contact_picture', 'Test Script Description': 'check USB Matrix status with status = USB_Matrix_Status().\nget serial numbers for them with HU, Mobile1 = get_serial_number().\ncreate recordings folder with create_recordings_folder() and start screen recording for HU with start_scre