ir_button() to unpair Mobile device with connected Bluetooth device.\nrun the following function on Mobile device: phone.disable_bluetooth() to disable Bluetooth of Mobile device.\nsave in Excel the status of the test (passed or failed) with the corresponding message.\nrun the following commmands after test is done in order to return to home menu: HU commands: adb shell input keyevent 3 one time; adb shell rm /sdcard/*.png; Mobile device commands: rc = phone.run_home_command().\nstop screen recordings on HU and Mobile after test is done with stop_screen_recording("HU") and keep them if test is failed or delete them if test is passed.'}, {'Test Case Description': '1 Put Mobile Device in shielding bag or shielding chamber or go out of range to simulate a linkloss\n2 Get Mobile Device out of shielding bag or shielding chamber or go in range.\n', 'Test Case Expected Result': '1 Bluetooth connection is released.\n2 Bluetooth connection is re-established.\n', 'Test Case ID': 172977, 'Test Case Precondition': 'Mobile Device and HU are connected.', 'Test Name': 'Mobile_Device_out_of_range', 'Test Script Description': 'check USB Matrix status with status = USB_Matrix_Status().\nget serial numbers for them with HU, Mobile1 = get_serial_number().\ncreate recordings folder with create_recordings_folder() and start screen recording for HU with start_screen_recording(f"-s {HU}", test_name, "HU")(example for HU).\nget Mobile device bluetooth name with adb shell settings get secure bluetooth_name.\nclick Bluetooth icon from HU display with x,y = find_icon_in_screenshot(f"{path}/screenshot.png",f"{path}/helpers/Bluetooth.png") or x,y = find_icon_in_screenshot(f"{path}/screenshot.png",f"{path}/helpers/Bluetooth_2.png").\nclick Manage Devices Button from HU display with found = click_on_device(HU,"Manage devices").\nclick Smartphones Button on from HU display with found = click_on_device(HU,"Smartphones").\ncreate Mobile device object with phone = create_device(Mobile1,mobile_name).\nrun the following function on Mobile device: phone.run_linkloss_command(). Wait 5 seconds with bluetooth module disabled.\nrun the following function on Mobile device: phone.run_linkloss_command(). Wait 15 seconds for bluetooth connection to be established.\ncheck if Connected word can be found on HU display with found = find_word_on_device(HU, "Connected"). If it was found then HU and Mobile device had been reconnected after link loss and the test is Passed. If not then HU and Mobile Device were disconnected after link loss and the test is failed.\nplease make a screenshot on HU screen and save it on the path D:\\traget\\IDCevo\\IOP_configuration\\Test_results\\Screenshots.\nsave in Excel the status of the test (passed or failed) with the message as in previous tests.\nrun the following commmands after test is done: HU command:adb shell input keyevent 3 one time; adb shell rm /sdcard/*.png.\nstop screen recordings on HU after test is done with stop_screen_recording("HU") and keep them if test is failed or delete them if test is passed.'}, {'Test Case Description': '1 Navigate to Communication -> Select Manage mobile devices.\nor\nPress COM button on ZBE.\n2 Scroll down to Settings and press ZBE.\n3 Go to Bluetooth and uncheIDCEvo the cheIDCEvobox.\n4 Wait 10 seconds.\n5 CheIDCEvo the cheIDCEvobox Bluetooth.\n', 'Test Case Expected Result': '3 Bluetooth connection is released.\n\n5 Bluetooth connection is re-established. \nMobil Device 1 is reconnected as Hands-Free Device 1, Audio and Apps (in case device was paired with apps and supports app-feature)\n', 'Test Case ID': 172976, 'Test Case Precondition': 'Mobile Device and HU are connected.', 'Test Name': 'HU_reconnect_after_Bluetooth_Off', 'Test Script Description': 'check USB Matrix status with status = USB_Matrix_Status().\nget serial numbers for them with HU, Mobile1 = get_serial_number().\ncreate recordings folder with create_recordings_folder() and start screen recording for HU with start_screen_recording(f"-s {HU}", test_name, "HU")(example for HU).\nget Mobile device bluetooth name with adb shell settings get secure bluetooth_name.\nclick Bluetooth icon from HU display with x,y = find_icon_in_screenshot(f"{path}/screenshot.png",f"{path}/helpers/Bluetooth.png") or x,y = find_icon_in_screenshot(f"{path}/screenshot.png",f"{path}/helpers/Bluetooth_2.png").\nclick Manage Devices Button from HU display with found = click_on_device(HU,"Manage devices").\nclick Smartphones Button on from HU display with found = click_on_device(HU,"Smartphones").\nclick Bluetooth icon from HU display with x,y = find_icon_in_screenshot(f"{path}/screenshot.png",f"{path}/helpers/Bluetooth.png") or x,y = find_icon_in_screenshot(f"{path}/screenshot.png",f"{path}/helpers/Bluetooth_2.png").\nclick Bluetooth word from HU display to disconnect Bluetooth with regex with found = click_on_device_regex(HU, "Bluetooth"). Wait 5 seconds with Bluetooth disconnected.\nclick Bluetooth word from HU display to reconnect Bluetooth with regex with found = click_on_device_regex(HU, "Bluetooth"). Wait 10 seconds.\ncheck if Connected word can be found on HU display with found = find_word_on_device(HU, "Connected"). If it was found then HU and Mobile device remained connected after HU Bluetooth off and the test is Passed. If not then HU and Mobile Device were disconnected after HU Bluetooth off and the test is failed.\nplease take a screenshot on HU screen and save it on the path D:\\traget\\IDCevo\\IOP_configuration\\Test_results\\Screenshots.\nsave in Excel the status of the test (passed or failed) with the corresponding message.\nrun the following commmands after test is done: HU command: adb shell input tap 400 300; adb shell input keyevent 3 one time; adb shell rm /sdcard/*.png.\nstop screen recordings on HU after test is done with stop_screen_recording("HU") and keep them if test is failed or delete them if test is passed.'}, {'Test Case Description': '1 Power Off HU while Bluetooth is ON.\nFor TestraIDCEvos and 