.\nrun the following function on Mobile device: rc = phone.dial_command(phone_number_mobile3) to initiate an outgoing call from Mobile Device 1 to Mobile Device 3. Wait 5 seconds for the call to start setting up.\ncheck USB Matrix status with status = USB_Matrix_Status(). If USB Matrix is connected to port 1 then change it to port 2 and if is connected to any other port except port1 change the connection to port 1.\nrun the following function on Mobile device3: rc = phone3.answer_call_command() to accept call on Mobile Device 3.\nswitch USB Matrix back to the port from the beginning with select_mobile_device(1, status).\nrun the following adb commands on HU: adb root; adb pull /data/misc/bluetooth/logs/btsnoop_hci.log btsnoop_hci_before_poweroff_outgoing.log; adb pull /data/misc/bluetooth/logs/btsnoop_hci.log.last btsnoop_hci_before_poweroff_outgoing.log.last; move btsnoop* D:/traget/IDCevo/IOP_configuration/Test_results in order to extract BTsnoop logs from HU before power off.\nrun the following function: power_off_HU() on HU to power off HU during the active outgoing call. Wait 10 seconds for HU to completely power off.\nrun the following function on Mobile device: rc = phone.run_turn_screen_on_command() to turn Mobile screen on.\nrun the following function on Mobile device: rc = phone.run_unlock_screen_command() to unlock Mobile screen.\nrun the following function on Mobile device: phone.run_settings_menu_command() go to Mobile Settings menu.\nrun the following function on Mobile device: rc = phone.run_bluetooth_menu_command() go to Mobile Bluetooth menu.\ncheck if bluetooth connection was released after HU power off with found = phone.check_bluetooth_connection(). If found contains the following text: ConnectionState: STATE_DISCONNECTED then Bluetooth connection was released and audio is still audible on Mobile Device and the test is Passed. If not then call was terminated and some implementations might hang up and the test is Failed.\nplease make a screenshot 